WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.458 --> 00:00:01.416
(SYRAX SCREECHES)

2
00:00:01.418 --> 00:00:05.006
You stand with a dragon
of House Targaryen!

3
00:00:05.088 --> 00:00:07.340
This dragon came to me.

4
00:00:07.757 --> 00:00:10.427
She wishes him to be instructed
in dragon riding.

5
00:00:10.677 --> 00:00:14.139
BARTIMOS CELTIGAR: The lowborn cannot
go around seizing dragons.

6
00:00:14.514 --> 00:00:17.976
With these riders.
we can end a needless war.

7
00:00:18.101 --> 00:00:19.853
House Targaryen is
the blood of the dragon.

8
00:00:20.311 --> 00:00:22.480
If any may lay claim to it.
what are we then?

9
00:00:22.689 --> 00:00:24.816
♪ (INTENSE MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

10
00:00:25.358 --> 00:00:27.360
We will make an alliance
with the Triarchy.

11
00:00:27.485 --> 00:00:29.612
I've had enough
of this cursed blockade.

12
00:00:29.654 --> 00:00:32.134
TYLAND LANNISTER: You cannot mean to treat
with the Free Cities.

13
00:00:35.118 --> 00:00:37.118
CRISTON COLE: I thank Your Grace
for her blessings.

14
00:00:38.872 --> 00:00:41.374
ALICENT HIGHTOWER: All my life.
I have endeavored to serve.

15
00:00:41.499 --> 00:00:42.876
and somehow none of it matters.

16
00:00:43.126 --> 00:00:45.211
Ser Rickard. I wish to go out.

17
00:00:49.382 --> 00:00:52.010
ALYS RIVERS: There are
older things in this world

18
00:00:52.052 --> 00:00:55.055
than you. or I.
or living memory.

19
00:00:55.555 --> 00:00:58.350
You are not the player.
but a piece on the board.

20
00:00:58.558 --> 00:01:02.812
Do you accept me
as your queen and ruler?

21
00:01:04.897 --> 00:01:06.149
I wish you to go to Harrenhal.

22
00:01:06.232 --> 00:01:07.859
Find out his intentions.

23
00:01:07.901 --> 00:01:10.653
Whether he means to raise a host
for me or for himself.

24
00:01:11.321 --> 00:01:13.656
I have received rumor
of the dragon Seasmoke

25
00:01:13.698 --> 00:01:14.741
with a rider.

26
00:01:15.700 --> 00:01:17.219
CORLYS VELARYON:
The rider is your brother.

27
00:01:17.243 --> 00:01:19.829
If it is something
in the blood...

28
00:01:20.038 --> 00:01:21.247
I am of salt and sea.

29
00:01:22.082 --> 00:01:23.541
I yearn for nothing else.

30
00:01:25.418 --> 00:01:26.896
RHAENA TARGARYEN:
You misled me. My Lady.

31
00:01:26.920 --> 00:01:28.838
There is a large dragon
in the Vale.

32
00:01:30.256 --> 00:01:33.218
JEYNE ARRYN:
It is large and formidable.

33
00:01:34.051 --> 00:01:35.553
But alas. wild.

34
00:01:36.054 --> 00:01:38.056
The Riverlands are held together
by oaths.

35
00:01:38.765 --> 00:01:40.326
DAEMON TARGARYEN: Then we shall
go to face your vassals.

36
00:01:40.350 --> 00:01:41.744
and you will call your banners
to war.

37
00:01:41.768 --> 00:01:43.853
OSCAR TULLY: There is a problem.
They all hate you.

38
00:01:44.229 --> 00:01:47.065
The old ways call for justice
to be done.

39
00:01:47.107 --> 00:01:48.108
Seize him.

40
00:01:48.274 --> 00:01:50.944
He must now rectify
his grievous error.

41
00:01:51.069 --> 00:01:52.862
No. no! No!

42
00:01:54.030 --> 00:01:55.782
It crushes whoever wears it.

43
00:01:55.907 --> 00:01:56.950
(PAINED GROAN)

44
00:01:57.033 --> 00:02:00.537
I push him on your instruction.
He is spent.

45
00:02:00.704 --> 00:02:02.848
LARYS STRONG: It will be long
before he may rest again.

46
00:02:02.872 --> 00:02:03.873
(PAINED GROAN)

47
00:02:04.708 --> 00:02:06.793
They're looking
for Targaryen bastards.

48
00:02:07.377 --> 00:02:10.213
RHAENYRA TARGARYEN: Each of you
has left behind a life

49
00:02:10.463 --> 00:02:12.924
to which you might never return.

50
00:02:13.758 --> 00:02:17.262
If you survive.
you will be transformed.

51
00:02:18.096 --> 00:02:19.764
The dragon. Vermithor...

52
00:02:22.142 --> 00:02:23.393
and Silverwing.

53
00:02:25.937 --> 00:02:27.772
Who among you would be first?

54
00:02:31.776 --> 00:02:33.903
(LAUGHS)

55
00:02:35.989 --> 00:02:41.494
(VHAGAR ROARS)

56
00:02:42.162 --> 00:02:44.789
RHAENYRA: Let us raise
an army of bastards.

57
00:02:44.831 --> 00:02:46.750
(DRAGON ROARS)

58
00:02:53.298 --> 00:02:56.468
(epic theme playing)

59
00:03:41.471 --> 00:03:43.682
♪♪

60
00:04:37.235 --> 00:04:39.237
(theme concludes)

61
00:04:41.239 --> 00:04:44.242
(tense music playing)

62
00:04:49.247 --> 00:04:52.042
(indistinct chatter)

63
00:04:52.125 --> 00:04:54.461
Tyroshi captain:
These are our terms.

64
00:04:54.586 --> 00:04:58.048
One hundred of your
golden dragons.

65
00:04:58.089 --> 00:05:01.051
- Tyland Lannister: Per ship?
- (captain chuckles)

66
00:05:01.092 --> 00:05:02.135
captain:
Per man.

67
00:05:02.260 --> 00:05:04.304
Tyland: I could not
produce such a coin.

68
00:05:04.429 --> 00:05:05.555
even if
I wanted to.

69
00:05:05.597 --> 00:05:07.197
Myrish captain:
Again. you plead poverty.

70
00:05:07.265 --> 00:05:10.268
It is hollow stuff
from the mouth of a Lannister.

71
00:05:10.310 --> 00:05:11.728
Whose very stables
and sculleries

72
00:05:11.770 --> 00:05:13.772
are carved into
a mountain of gold.

73
00:05:13.813 --> 00:05:16.733
And we will need it
before this war is done.

74
00:05:16.775 --> 00:05:19.444
Break the blockade
and it will benefit you.

75
00:05:19.569 --> 00:05:21.446
Do you think that we lack
for buyers

76
00:05:21.488 --> 00:05:23.907
for our tapestries
and perfumes?

77
00:05:23.948 --> 00:05:26.284
We sell where
we please.

78
00:05:26.409 --> 00:05:27.786
blockade or no.

79
00:05:28.328 --> 00:05:30.955
Essos is as rich
as it is vast.

80
00:05:30.997 --> 00:05:35.418
It seems you need us
more than we need you.

81
00:05:35.460 --> 00:05:38.296
- (sighs)
- (indistinct chatter)

82
00:05:39.297 --> 00:05:40.674
The Stepstones.

83
00:05:42.926 --> 00:05:44.969
(scoffs)
What of them?

84
00:05:45.303 --> 00:05:46.971
Give us the Stepstones.

85
00:05:47.972 --> 00:05:49.641
A smattering
of rocks...

86
00:05:50.350 --> 00:05:53.812
hardly a sacrifice
to the lords of Westeros.

87
00:05:53.937 --> 00:05:59.150
I... Those rocks have been
disputed for a generation.

88
00:06:00.443 --> 00:06:01.611
Your...

89
00:06:02.320 --> 00:06:06.324
pirates have waylaid ships.
taken slaves. cargo...

90
00:06:06.366 --> 00:06:09.327
Give them to us outright.
if you prevail.

91
00:06:09.369 --> 00:06:11.705
and all that
will cease.

92
00:06:11.830 --> 00:06:13.498
We will impose
a simple tax

93
00:06:13.540 --> 00:06:15.125
on those
passing through.

94
00:06:15.166 --> 00:06:17.544
Recoup the losses
we took fighting

95
00:06:17.669 --> 00:06:19.146
- the Velaryon hordes.
- Tyland: Extortion.

96
00:06:19.170 --> 00:06:21.047
You will drive up
the price of basic goods.

97
00:06:21.172 --> 00:06:24.843
It is better than
starving. surely.

98
00:06:28.179 --> 00:06:31.141
Myrish captain: A fleet of warships. then.
sailing at your command.

99
00:06:31.182 --> 00:06:33.476
- They would break the blockade...
- Tyland: Hm.

100
00:06:33.518 --> 00:06:35.186
...and hold
the passage.

101
00:06:40.859 --> 00:06:42.193
Very well.

102
00:06:45.864 --> 00:06:48.658
The prince regent may
have me hanged for this.

103
00:06:48.700 --> 00:06:50.659
With the armada
we send now.

104
00:06:50.702 --> 00:06:52.996
you can topple
the prince regent

105
00:06:53.038 --> 00:06:55.373
and sit
the Iron Throne yourself.

106
00:06:59.419 --> 00:07:04.174
- (grunts)
- Myrish captain: Of course. there is one more condition.

107
00:07:04.215 --> 00:07:05.383
(sighs)

108
00:07:06.676 --> 00:07:07.886
Tyland:
I was...

109
00:07:07.927 --> 00:07:10.347
rather set on a bath
and a flagon of wine.

110
00:07:10.388 --> 00:07:11.907
Myrish captain:
The commander of our fleet

111
00:07:11.931 --> 00:07:13.266
must agree
to go with you.

112
00:07:13.391 --> 00:07:16.394
His name is Lohar.
The sailors are fiercely loyal to him.

113
00:07:16.519 --> 00:07:17.854
If. if he does
not lead them.

114
00:07:17.896 --> 00:07:19.773
they will not fight.

115
00:07:22.233 --> 00:07:23.401
Very well.

116
00:07:23.902 --> 00:07:26.863
Let us meet this
commander then.

117
00:07:27.697 --> 00:07:29.908
(clears throat. grunts)

118
00:07:29.949 --> 00:07:33.203
- (flies buzzing)
- (indistinct chatter)

119
00:07:37.749 --> 00:07:39.125
Admiral Lohar...

120
00:07:40.085 --> 00:07:42.420
this is
Tyland Lannister.

121
00:07:42.462 --> 00:07:44.381
of Casterly Rock.

122
00:07:45.090 --> 00:07:47.884
Well met.
Lord Tywin.

123
00:07:48.468 --> 00:07:49.886
Uh...

124
00:07:52.138 --> 00:07:54.140
it's Tyland.

125
00:07:55.767 --> 00:07:57.560
What sort of
man are you?

126
00:07:58.937 --> 00:08:02.273
- I beg your pardon?
- A poet...

127
00:08:03.274 --> 00:08:04.484
a philosopher?

128
00:08:04.943 --> 00:08:07.654
I am the master of ships
at King's Landing.

129
00:08:08.113 --> 00:08:11.449
- You're thin.
- But also tall.

130
00:08:13.952 --> 00:08:17.455
I will not sail with a man
who cannot best me.

131
00:08:17.580 --> 00:08:19.749
(quiet laughter)

132
00:08:19.791 --> 00:08:22.002
(indistinct chatter)

133
00:08:23.294 --> 00:08:24.963
At. at what?

134
00:08:27.799 --> 00:08:30.760
(tense music playing)

135
00:08:30.802 --> 00:08:34.014
(grumbles. roars)

136
00:08:45.775 --> 00:08:48.987
♪♪

137
00:08:55.035 --> 00:08:57.996
(people wailing. screaming)

138
00:09:07.505 --> 00:09:09.841
(music fades out)

139
00:09:10.675 --> 00:09:12.844
(Orwyle pouring tea)

140
00:09:14.137 --> 00:09:16.348
Some rum wouldn't go amiss.

141
00:09:17.515 --> 00:09:19.059
Your Grace.

142
00:09:19.684 --> 00:09:21.978
Just a little.

143
00:09:22.020 --> 00:09:24.397
(distant bell tolling)

144
00:09:29.861 --> 00:09:32.238
You're a good man.
Orwyle.

145
00:09:36.409 --> 00:09:37.702
(door opens)

146
00:09:37.827 --> 00:09:40.038
(Aegon drinking)

147
00:09:42.749 --> 00:09:44.709
(birds chirping)

148
00:09:44.834 --> 00:09:46.211
A word. Your Grace?

149
00:09:47.212 --> 00:09:50.382
(exhales. clears throat)

150
00:10:04.396 --> 00:10:06.189
(door closes)

151
00:10:06.231 --> 00:10:09.359
I must ask you.
Your Grace. to steel yourself.

152
00:10:10.235 --> 00:10:12.278
We must leave
King's Landing. quickly.

153
00:10:12.404 --> 00:10:15.031
and we will not return
for some time.

154
00:10:16.574 --> 00:10:21.079
- What?
- The Pretender has found three new riders for her dragons.

155
00:10:21.204 --> 00:10:24.374
- That's impossible.
- Your brother thought the same.

156
00:10:24.416 --> 00:10:27.252
He flew to challenge her
and was rebuffed.

157
00:10:27.377 --> 00:10:29.587
Fled in terror.
from what I hear.

158
00:10:31.756 --> 00:10:33.425
He deserves no less.

159
00:10:33.633 --> 00:10:37.887
Be that as it may.
he has gone in fury to Sharp Point...

160
00:10:38.430 --> 00:10:41.266
and laid waste
to the whole of the town.

161
00:10:42.600 --> 00:10:45.145
Fucking mad cunt.

162
00:10:47.605 --> 00:10:49.232
She really
did it then?

163
00:10:49.774 --> 00:10:51.443
I fear so.

164
00:10:52.777 --> 00:10:56.114
So. what was the fucking point
in all this then?

165
00:10:57.157 --> 00:10:59.325
The gods are cruel.
Your Grace.

166
00:10:59.409 --> 00:11:02.954
but I hope
you can see the urgency.

167
00:11:02.996 --> 00:11:08.126
No. no. I am the king.
Why must I run?

168
00:11:08.460 --> 00:11:11.254
Because the prince regent
is going to kill you.

169
00:11:15.300 --> 00:11:16.426
You were
in danger before.

170
00:11:16.468 --> 00:11:19.929
and now. he is thwarted
and he is angry.

171
00:11:19.971 --> 00:11:21.324
There is no telling
what he will do.

172
00:11:21.348 --> 00:11:22.807
but we have
an opportunity

173
00:11:22.932 --> 00:11:26.311
- while he is away...
- An opportunity to push him out.

174
00:11:26.978 --> 00:11:28.772
Take me to my throne

175
00:11:28.813 --> 00:11:33.443
and once he returns.
I shall take him prisoner... hm?

176
00:11:33.485 --> 00:11:36.154
And what then?

177
00:11:36.196 --> 00:11:38.782
When Rhaenyra descends
on you with her seven dragons.

178
00:11:38.823 --> 00:11:41.201
and you. without Vhagar.
what then?

179
00:11:42.827 --> 00:11:43.995
W...

180
00:11:44.871 --> 00:11:46.164
Uh...

181
00:11:52.671 --> 00:11:54.130
I have.
over the years.

182
00:11:54.172 --> 00:11:56.508
in anticipation
of little bumps in the road.

183
00:11:56.633 --> 00:11:59.302
moved the greater part
of Harrenhal's gold reserves

184
00:11:59.344 --> 00:12:01.513
to the Iron Bank
in Braavos.

185
00:12:01.638 --> 00:12:04.015
We can live... well

186
00:12:04.140 --> 00:12:07.644
and remain until
what is coming has passed.

187
00:12:07.686 --> 00:12:09.688
(weak laughter)

188
00:12:10.188 --> 00:12:13.483
Y... You want
to take me to Essos

189
00:12:13.525 --> 00:12:15.694
to live with
the goatfuckers.

190
00:12:16.861 --> 00:12:18.863
It's best to live.
I think.

191
00:12:19.155 --> 00:12:21.533
- However you do it.
- Is it?

192
00:12:23.243 --> 00:12:25.870
My dragon is dead.

193
00:12:25.995 --> 00:12:27.997
I am burnt...

194
00:12:28.039 --> 00:12:31.710
and disgusting...
and alone.

195
00:12:32.585 --> 00:12:34.212
And I'm a cripple.

196
00:12:37.716 --> 00:12:39.050
You are not alone.

197
00:12:39.092 --> 00:12:41.845
My cock is destroyed.
did they tell you that?

198
00:12:41.886 --> 00:12:45.932
Yeah. It burst into flames
like a sausage on the spit.

199
00:12:46.057 --> 00:12:47.392
Do not despair.
Your Grace.

200
00:12:47.434 --> 00:12:49.602
There are
better days ahead.

201
00:12:49.894 --> 00:12:52.230
Let your brother
and the Pretender

202
00:12:52.355 --> 00:12:55.525
destroy themselves
in blood and bitterness.

203
00:12:55.567 --> 00:12:56.860
When they are spent.

204
00:12:56.901 --> 00:12:58.445
and their armies
in tatters.

205
00:12:58.570 --> 00:12:59.696
we will return.

206
00:12:59.738 --> 00:13:03.199
and the people
will rise up to meet us.

207
00:13:03.241 --> 00:13:06.244
I can't even piss
without it running down my leg.

208
00:13:06.286 --> 00:13:11.207
They will be tired
of endless deprivation and fear.

209
00:13:12.292 --> 00:13:15.712
They will hail
the returning king...

210
00:13:15.754 --> 00:13:18.590
his father's true heir.

211
00:13:19.924 --> 00:13:22.761
Aegon
the Victorious...

212
00:13:22.886 --> 00:13:24.888
risen from the ashes.

213
00:13:25.930 --> 00:13:28.099
Aegon the Peacemaker.

214
00:13:30.935 --> 00:13:33.146
Aegon the Rebuilder.

215
00:13:36.399 --> 00:13:39.277
Aegon. the Realm's Delight.

216
00:13:41.112 --> 00:13:44.449
- (tense music playing)
- (wind blowing)

217
00:13:49.287 --> 00:13:51.456
(heavy breathing)

218
00:13:53.792 --> 00:13:55.794
(water flowing)

219
00:14:11.643 --> 00:14:12.644
(gasps)

220
00:14:24.197 --> 00:14:26.199
♪♪

221
00:14:26.783 --> 00:14:29.703
Ulf: This is more like it.
Hugh. don't you think?

222
00:14:29.828 --> 00:14:32.181
Hugh: We're meant to be
at the training yards learnin' the commands.

223
00:14:32.205 --> 00:14:33.665
Ulf:
Yeah. and I will go.

224
00:14:33.790 --> 00:14:37.210
but surely they'd not deny me
my pleasure after so long.

225
00:14:37.335 --> 00:14:40.171
- I may never eat fish again.
- (music fades out)

226
00:14:40.880 --> 00:14:42.674
What are you
doing here?

227
00:14:43.049 --> 00:14:44.467
Remove your feet
from the table.

228
00:14:44.509 --> 00:14:46.302
- Ulf: I'd rather not.
- Hugh: Ulf.

229
00:14:46.344 --> 00:14:49.014
It's not up
to you... Ulf.

230
00:14:49.139 --> 00:14:51.975
Who's it up
to then... boy?

231
00:14:52.017 --> 00:14:55.520
He is the prince. Ulf.
Prince Jacaerys Velaryon.

232
00:14:56.354 --> 00:15:00.150
Prince Jacaerys Velaryon.
Right here. (chuckles)

233
00:15:00.191 --> 00:15:01.860
Who'd have
thought it?

234
00:15:01.901 --> 00:15:02.902
He lives here.

235
00:15:03.528 --> 00:15:05.989
I'll have
an apology from you.

236
00:15:06.031 --> 00:15:08.324
Ah!
The young prince!

237
00:15:08.366 --> 00:15:10.493
And look
at that hair.

238
00:15:12.078 --> 00:15:13.872
As dark as they say.

239
00:15:14.706 --> 00:15:17.208
Let them tell us
we don't have Targaryen blood. eh?

240
00:15:17.834 --> 00:15:21.546
- My mother is the queen and...
- Dragonriders both.

241
00:15:21.671 --> 00:15:24.883
You and I...
cut from the same cloth.

242
00:15:24.924 --> 00:15:28.887
It is a sacred inheritance
of which you know nothing.

243
00:15:28.928 --> 00:15:30.555
Forgive him.
my prince.

244
00:15:30.680 --> 00:15:33.058
He is not much
used to the manners of court.

245
00:15:33.558 --> 00:15:35.352
Or any manners
at all. I'd say.

246
00:15:35.393 --> 00:15:38.730
Do you know what has happened
this last hour. hm?

247
00:15:39.689 --> 00:15:41.358
The so-called
prince regent

248
00:15:41.399 --> 00:15:43.234
has burned Sharp Point
down to its stones.

249
00:15:43.360 --> 00:15:45.362
Thousands of its folk
dead or lost.

250
00:15:45.403 --> 00:15:48.198
Its harbor in ashes.

251
00:15:48.239 --> 00:15:50.950
Will you prepare
to face such an enemy?

252
00:15:52.410 --> 00:15:55.246
Or will you stay here
and make yourself easy?

253
00:15:55.288 --> 00:15:57.457
If you hinder
our efforts

254
00:15:57.582 --> 00:15:59.959
through sloth
or unreadiness.

255
00:16:00.085 --> 00:16:01.252
I will see
you hanged.

256
00:16:01.294 --> 00:16:03.797
and your body fed to the dogs
in the street.

257
00:16:04.589 --> 00:16:07.759
I-I meant no disrespect.
my prince.

258
00:16:22.440 --> 00:16:23.900
(indistinct chatter)

259
00:16:23.942 --> 00:16:26.403
Rhaenyra Targaryen:
The new riders are a boon to us.

260
00:16:26.444 --> 00:16:28.947
but now
the deed is done.

261
00:16:28.988 --> 00:16:31.574
I cannot erase
my doubts.

262
00:16:32.117 --> 00:16:33.576
We know little
of who they are.

263
00:16:33.618 --> 00:16:36.454
and what is the strength
of their character.

264
00:16:36.579 --> 00:16:38.790
Addam of Hull. at least.
is known to you.

265
00:16:40.125 --> 00:16:42.085
He's a shipwright
in my employ.

266
00:16:42.127 --> 00:16:45.797
and it is reported to me that
he is a man of integrity.

267
00:16:45.922 --> 00:16:50.468
I've had little to do with him...
to my regret.

268
00:16:51.136 --> 00:16:53.430
But the beasts
have been claimed.

269
00:16:53.471 --> 00:16:55.974
You now have
a great advantage.

270
00:16:56.016 --> 00:16:57.934
You must strike.
quickly.

271
00:16:57.976 --> 00:17:00.478
while the prince regent
mulls his next action.

272
00:17:01.813 --> 00:17:05.858
I had hoped my advantage
may be in deterrence.

273
00:17:05.983 --> 00:17:07.694
Vhagar has ever been
our foremost threat.

274
00:17:07.819 --> 00:17:09.695
and she is now
overmatched.

275
00:17:09.820 --> 00:17:11.489
Vhagar is not
his only dragon.

276
00:17:11.531 --> 00:17:13.324
W... The third brother
is untested.

277
00:17:13.450 --> 00:17:14.659
has never
left Oldtown.

278
00:17:14.784 --> 00:17:16.953
and his dragon is
younger than Vermax.

279
00:17:16.994 --> 00:17:18.496
But a dragon
nonetheless.

280
00:17:18.538 --> 00:17:20.665
And you forget another.

281
00:17:22.166 --> 00:17:23.335
Helaena?

282
00:17:23.835 --> 00:17:26.296
She does not ride.
She has no taste for it.

283
00:17:26.338 --> 00:17:28.506
She may yet
be compelled.

284
00:17:28.548 --> 00:17:30.383
- And her dragon...
- Dreamfyre.

285
00:17:30.508 --> 00:17:32.844
hatched when
the Conqueror was king.

286
00:17:33.970 --> 00:17:35.638
She is formidable.

287
00:17:35.680 --> 00:17:38.058
Still. Helaena
is no warrior.

288
00:17:41.186 --> 00:17:43.521
Aemond thought
himself invincible.

289
00:17:43.563 --> 00:17:46.191
He has now discovered
he is not.

290
00:17:46.316 --> 00:17:48.485
He'll be angry.
desperate.

291
00:17:48.985 --> 00:17:51.321
He will not stop
at burning Sharp Point.

292
00:17:51.363 --> 00:17:53.698
and he will
not be denied.

293
00:17:54.366 --> 00:17:55.825
You speak truly...

294
00:17:56.743 --> 00:17:58.495
though I wish it
was not so.

295
00:17:58.536 --> 00:18:00.997
(soft chuckle)

296
00:18:01.039 --> 00:18:03.041
(indistinct chatter)

297
00:18:03.500 --> 00:18:05.001
How goes
the Sea Snake?

298
00:18:06.503 --> 00:18:08.213
Better than new.

299
00:18:08.880 --> 00:18:10.882
We'll rejoin the blockade
on the morrow.

300
00:18:11.216 --> 00:18:14.886
Let our foes beware.
be they Lannister or Greyjoy.

301
00:18:16.346 --> 00:18:20.058
But... my ship is no longer
the Sea Snake.

302
00:18:20.392 --> 00:18:23.687
She was a testament
to my own glory.

303
00:18:23.770 --> 00:18:26.022
I've given her
a new name.

304
00:18:28.233 --> 00:18:30.610
The Queen Who Never Was.

305
00:18:33.071 --> 00:18:34.239
Rhaenyra:
Corlys...

306
00:18:35.365 --> 00:18:37.075
I thank you.

307
00:18:39.577 --> 00:18:41.204
(soft chuckle)

308
00:18:41.246 --> 00:18:44.916
What I do now...
I do for her.

309
00:18:47.460 --> 00:18:49.462
Your Grace.
you are ready.

310
00:18:49.587 --> 00:18:52.590
You have six dragons
under your banner.

311
00:18:53.133 --> 00:18:55.385
My ships sail
at your command.

312
00:18:55.427 --> 00:18:57.053
and my men serve you.

313
00:18:57.595 --> 00:18:59.556
But the Lannisters
are marching.

314
00:18:59.597 --> 00:19:02.267
and the Hightowers
from Oldtown.

315
00:19:02.392 --> 00:19:06.479
You must crush this beast
at its head

316
00:19:06.604 --> 00:19:09.107
and before too many
days have flown.

317
00:19:12.318 --> 00:19:14.154
There is.
of course...

318
00:19:14.279 --> 00:19:17.949
another player that has yet
to be revealed.

319
00:19:19.784 --> 00:19:21.786
Ah. Your Grace.
a word.

320
00:19:21.828 --> 00:19:25.123
It seems the sheep
on our land has been sold upriver.

321
00:19:25.248 --> 00:19:28.168
My vassals have sent a drove
of swine instead.

322
00:19:28.293 --> 00:19:29.794
Dragons do eat pigs.
I assume?

323
00:19:29.919 --> 00:19:32.130
Caraxes prefers them.
How goes your muster?

324
00:19:32.172 --> 00:19:33.774
We'll be ready to march
in two days' time.

325
00:19:33.798 --> 00:19:35.967
- See to those pigs.
- At once. Your Grace.

326
00:19:36.009 --> 00:19:39.971
Your Grace... Ser Alfred Broome
has come to see you.

327
00:19:40.096 --> 00:19:42.432
(laughs) Interesting.

328
00:19:42.474 --> 00:19:44.434
I am sent as an emissary
from the queen.

329
00:19:44.476 --> 00:19:46.770
to ascertain your movements
and your intentions.

330
00:19:46.853 --> 00:19:48.188
You've arrived
just in time

331
00:19:48.313 --> 00:19:50.690
to see my new
army. Broome.

332
00:19:50.815 --> 00:19:52.484
What do you
think of it?

333
00:19:52.525 --> 00:19:54.319
It's very large.

334
00:19:54.361 --> 00:19:56.488
(Daemon chuckles softly)

335
00:19:56.529 --> 00:19:58.531
Lannister hesitates.

336
00:19:58.948 --> 00:20:01.659
I aim to march on King's Landing
before he can catch me.

337
00:20:01.785 --> 00:20:04.662
May I have a word in private.
Your Grace?

338
00:20:09.000 --> 00:20:11.002
I would speak
honestly with you.

339
00:20:11.044 --> 00:20:12.480
Daemon Targaryen:
I'd expect nothing less.

340
00:20:12.504 --> 00:20:15.507
Alfred Broome: I was faithful to the king.
your brother.

341
00:20:15.632 --> 00:20:18.176
I pledged my banners
to Rhaenyra. his heir.

342
00:20:18.301 --> 00:20:19.886
I will never serve
the usurpers

343
00:20:20.011 --> 00:20:21.846
or the whelps
of Oldtown.

344
00:20:21.888 --> 00:20:23.848
but there are battles
to be fought...

345
00:20:23.973 --> 00:20:26.851
- voice (whispers): Traitor.
- ...and in times like this...

346
00:20:29.688 --> 00:20:31.648
Did you hear
something?

347
00:20:33.191 --> 00:20:36.069
This place will have you barking
at the moon.

348
00:20:38.863 --> 00:20:40.657
While you have
mustered an army.

349
00:20:40.699 --> 00:20:42.492
Rhaenyra
has faltered...

350
00:20:42.534 --> 00:20:44.160
turning aside
from our judgment.

351
00:20:44.202 --> 00:20:46.413
and taking a course.
I myself. deem reckless.

352
00:20:46.538 --> 00:20:50.667
Rhaenyra will chart her own course.
for good or ill.

353
00:20:50.709 --> 00:20:52.877
But you are
a leader of men.

354
00:20:54.170 --> 00:20:56.506
If you declare
yourself.

355
00:20:56.548 --> 00:20:58.425
your lords
will follow you.

356
00:20:58.883 --> 00:21:01.928
I never took you
for a turncloak...

357
00:21:02.721 --> 00:21:04.597
Ser Alfred.

358
00:21:07.350 --> 00:21:09.728
Rhaenyra's
intentions are good.

359
00:21:11.104 --> 00:21:15.066
But what we need.
in this moment...

360
00:21:16.568 --> 00:21:18.069
is a king.

361
00:21:20.613 --> 00:21:24.117
(tense music playing)

362
00:21:24.242 --> 00:21:25.910
(chuckles)

363
00:21:36.546 --> 00:21:37.881
(sighs)

364
00:21:37.922 --> 00:21:39.924
♪♪

365
00:21:44.763 --> 00:21:46.574
Jasper "Ironrod" Wylde:
It appears that the Pretender

366
00:21:46.598 --> 00:21:48.242
sent boats to collect
those among the smallfolk

367
00:21:48.266 --> 00:21:50.894
who believed they had any drop
of Targaryen blood.

368
00:21:50.935 --> 00:21:52.937
Deception
and subterfuge.

369
00:21:53.063 --> 00:21:56.107
Cowards. all of them.
Put an end to this madness.

370
00:21:56.149 --> 00:21:59.319
Let no vessel come or go from our harbor
without our inspection.

371
00:21:59.444 --> 00:22:01.780
This will hinder the work
of the fishing boats.

372
00:22:01.905 --> 00:22:03.907
The people depend on them
for sustenance.

373
00:22:03.948 --> 00:22:05.617
They will need
no sustenance

374
00:22:05.742 --> 00:22:07.952
if they are slaughtered
by the enemy.

375
00:22:07.994 --> 00:22:10.413
We must all make
our sacrifices.

376
00:22:12.832 --> 00:22:15.085
Helaena Targaryen:
Why does everybody hate us?

377
00:22:15.126 --> 00:22:17.087
Alicent Hightower:
They're unhappy...

378
00:22:17.128 --> 00:22:19.923
and unhappy people look
for someone to hate.

379
00:22:23.426 --> 00:22:25.136
We didn't order
the blockade.

380
00:22:25.261 --> 00:22:28.682
No. but we are the crown.
so they expect us to break it.

381
00:22:29.808 --> 00:22:31.142
Drink this.

382
00:22:38.149 --> 00:22:40.985
I was happier
before I was queen.

383
00:22:47.283 --> 00:22:49.994
What would you think
about leaving this place?

384
00:22:52.664 --> 00:22:54.833
(birds cawing)

385
00:22:58.670 --> 00:23:00.672
Where would I go?

386
00:23:00.714 --> 00:23:02.966
(knocks on door)

387
00:23:06.970 --> 00:23:08.513
The prince regent.
Your Grace.

388
00:23:08.555 --> 00:23:11.349
Helaena. Here you are.
Mother.

389
00:23:13.727 --> 00:23:17.230
- I was just. just going to bed.
- The crown has need of your service.

390
00:23:17.355 --> 00:23:19.858
- Now?
- The Pretender has raised new riders against us.

391
00:23:19.983 --> 00:23:23.737
and we must
answer in kind.

392
00:23:23.862 --> 00:23:25.655
I need you to fly
with Dreamfyre to battle.

393
00:23:25.697 --> 00:23:27.574
- Aemond.
- I do not wish to fight.

394
00:23:27.699 --> 00:23:29.826
Our wishes must take
second place now

395
00:23:29.868 --> 00:23:32.746
to what is necessary
to preserve the throne.

396
00:23:33.496 --> 00:23:35.498
I won't burn anyone.

397
00:23:37.542 --> 00:23:38.835
It isn't a question.

398
00:23:38.877 --> 00:23:40.521
- Aemond.
- They have defiled our birthright.

399
00:23:40.545 --> 00:23:42.225
- made commoners into dragonlords!
- Ow. ow!

400
00:23:42.255 --> 00:23:43.691
- Aemond! Aemond!
- It is a sin and must be punished!

401
00:23:43.715 --> 00:23:45.693
- May I remind you your sister is still the queen?
- Ow!

402
00:23:45.717 --> 00:23:47.594
As you were once!
And you see now

403
00:23:47.719 --> 00:23:49.196
what is the consequence
of your weakness!

404
00:23:49.220 --> 00:23:51.222
We are in peril today
more than yesterday!

405
00:23:51.348 --> 00:23:53.933
Was it peril that moved you to burn
the town of Sharp Point?

406
00:23:54.059 --> 00:23:56.686
Peril or basest fury
at your own humiliation?

407
00:23:56.728 --> 00:23:57.728
Ow!

408
00:23:58.396 --> 00:23:59.856
You wish to rule
the Seven Kingdoms.

409
00:23:59.898 --> 00:24:02.400
but you rain ruin and death
upon its smallfolk

410
00:24:02.442 --> 00:24:04.527
when you've
been insulted

411
00:24:04.569 --> 00:24:06.279
because it makes
you feel strong

412
00:24:06.404 --> 00:24:08.198
and now you seek
to corrupt your sister.

413
00:24:08.239 --> 00:24:10.408
of all our line.
the gentlest and most deserving

414
00:24:10.533 --> 00:24:12.053
- of your protection.
- And who will protect her

415
00:24:12.077 --> 00:24:13.244
if she cannot
protect herself?

416
00:24:13.286 --> 00:24:14.889
And who will she be
if her mind is broken?!

417
00:24:14.913 --> 00:24:16.915
'Tis no longer our rule
that is threatened.

418
00:24:16.956 --> 00:24:18.083
our very lives.

419
00:24:18.208 --> 00:24:20.251
- Would you not have us prevail?
- Not like this.

420
00:24:23.755 --> 00:24:25.882
Not like this!

421
00:24:27.217 --> 00:24:30.595
(light. tense music playing)

422
00:24:42.607 --> 00:24:44.109
Grand Maester Orwyle:
Your Grace.

423
00:24:44.776 --> 00:24:46.111
Grand Maester.

424
00:24:47.278 --> 00:24:49.823
I must again request
your assistance.

425
00:24:50.448 --> 00:24:52.117
I need passage.

426
00:24:52.909 --> 00:24:54.953
And your discretion.

427
00:24:57.622 --> 00:25:00.917
(solemn music playing)

428
00:25:00.959 --> 00:25:04.170
- (quiet chatter)
- (ambient nature sounds)

429
00:25:06.506 --> 00:25:09.634
Gwayne Hightower: Do you think
nothing of your oath...

430
00:25:11.636 --> 00:25:13.138
Lord Commander?

431
00:25:15.098 --> 00:25:17.350
I think of nothing
else. my lord.

432
00:25:18.643 --> 00:25:20.854
Steward's son
from Dorne

433
00:25:20.979 --> 00:25:23.815
fucking the queen
of the Seven Kingdoms.

434
00:25:25.650 --> 00:25:27.360
Former queen.

435
00:25:28.153 --> 00:25:30.113
She has broken no oath.
for all I may have done.

436
00:25:30.155 --> 00:25:32.991
- I could send you to the Wall.
- You could.

437
00:25:33.033 --> 00:25:36.036
Stain the Hightower name
for a generation.

438
00:25:36.453 --> 00:25:39.497
- King's mother and his Hand.
- She is my sister.

439
00:25:41.207 --> 00:25:42.334
(inhales)

440
00:25:42.459 --> 00:25:44.336
She saved my life.

441
00:25:45.337 --> 00:25:46.463
Twice.

442
00:25:46.504 --> 00:25:49.507
Once from the headsman's axe
and once from myself.

443
00:25:53.011 --> 00:25:55.889
Since then. she has been
the beacon I follow.

444
00:26:05.190 --> 00:26:09.152
Do not think I have
no shame in me. ser.

445
00:26:09.194 --> 00:26:12.030
Desire for women
has brought me grief after grief.

446
00:26:12.530 --> 00:26:16.034
- Gwayne: Then resist it.
- (Criston chuckles softly)

447
00:26:16.701 --> 00:26:18.244
Oh. would that
it were so simple.

448
00:26:18.370 --> 00:26:21.331
Your brothers
in the Kingsguard find a way.

449
00:26:24.417 --> 00:26:26.044
Do they?

450
00:26:27.545 --> 00:26:29.339
Mm. perhaps
they do.

451
00:26:31.049 --> 00:26:33.593
Or perhaps all men
are corrupt...

452
00:26:35.220 --> 00:26:37.931
and true honor is a mist

453
00:26:38.723 --> 00:26:40.225
that melts in the morning.

454
00:26:42.727 --> 00:26:45.063
That is a bleak philosophy.

455
00:26:45.438 --> 00:26:47.357
I have no philosophy.

456
00:26:48.400 --> 00:26:50.944
Or rather.
my philosophy was this.

457
00:26:53.071 --> 00:26:54.280
To protect
the righteous

458
00:26:54.364 --> 00:26:57.075
and dispense justice
on the rest.

459
00:26:59.035 --> 00:27:00.412
But now...

460
00:27:03.623 --> 00:27:05.542
You saw what I saw.

461
00:27:10.588 --> 00:27:14.926
The dragons dance.
and men are like dust under their feet.

462
00:27:18.263 --> 00:27:21.808
And all our fine thoughts.
all our... endeavors

463
00:27:21.933 --> 00:27:23.601
are as nothing.

464
00:27:29.274 --> 00:27:32.402
We march now toward
our annihilation.

465
00:27:38.783 --> 00:27:41.411
To die will be
a kind of relief.

466
00:27:45.832 --> 00:27:47.459
Don't you think?

467
00:27:54.674 --> 00:27:57.677
(unsettling music playing)

468
00:28:21.368 --> 00:28:23.119
- (Sharako yells)
- (crowd cheering)

469
00:28:23.161 --> 00:28:25.330
(heavy breathing. grunts)

470
00:28:25.372 --> 00:28:27.999
- (crowd shouting)
- (Sharako laughing)

471
00:28:31.836 --> 00:28:34.005
(crowd shouting. laughing)

472
00:28:34.297 --> 00:28:36.716
(Tyland yells. pants)

473
00:28:38.551 --> 00:28:40.637
(Tyland grunting)

474
00:28:42.514 --> 00:28:43.723
(Sharako laughs)

475
00:28:45.642 --> 00:28:47.644
(yells. grunts)

476
00:28:49.187 --> 00:28:51.356
(heavy breathing)

477
00:28:54.734 --> 00:28:56.486
(groaning)

478
00:29:01.032 --> 00:29:02.367
(laughs)

479
00:29:02.701 --> 00:29:04.994
(crowd chanting "Lohar")

480
00:29:05.036 --> 00:29:06.538
(grunting)

481
00:29:08.498 --> 00:29:09.666
(crowd quiets)

482
00:29:09.708 --> 00:29:11.376
- (grunts)
- (Sharako yelps)

483
00:29:13.545 --> 00:29:15.547
(heavy breathing)

484
00:29:16.423 --> 00:29:18.425
(all silent)

485
00:29:20.427 --> 00:29:21.427
(spits)

486
00:29:26.891 --> 00:29:29.060
You have impressed me.
Lord Tyman.

487
00:29:29.894 --> 00:29:33.690
King's Landing
has sent a most doughty ambassador.

488
00:29:33.732 --> 00:29:35.400
(panting)

489
00:29:36.568 --> 00:29:42.365
I hope... you will testify to the worth
of the ambassador...

490
00:29:42.407 --> 00:29:46.202
by agreeing to his most
(pants) humble request.

491
00:29:46.244 --> 00:29:49.414
I will
most certainly consider it.

492
00:29:50.081 --> 00:29:51.124
(spits)

493
00:29:56.755 --> 00:29:58.590
After dinner.

494
00:30:02.719 --> 00:30:05.597
Have you ever eaten
the flesh of your enemies?

495
00:30:05.638 --> 00:30:07.390
(panting)
What?

496
00:30:09.434 --> 00:30:12.604
I have not
and I would not.

497
00:30:14.147 --> 00:30:18.735
So you reject
the hospitality of my house.

498
00:30:26.451 --> 00:30:29.496
- (laughs)
- (crowd laughs)

499
00:30:29.621 --> 00:30:30.914
A jest. my lord.

500
00:30:32.123 --> 00:30:35.251
(laughing)
What do you take me for?

501
00:30:38.088 --> 00:30:39.464
A jest!

502
00:30:40.465 --> 00:30:41.633
Come.

503
00:30:44.969 --> 00:30:47.806
- (grunts)
- (crowd yells. laughs)

504
00:30:52.352 --> 00:30:54.771
(nearby dragon grumbles)

505
00:30:56.314 --> 00:30:58.858
It does not befit
a prince to pout.

506
00:31:00.694 --> 00:31:02.153
I'm not pouting.

507
00:31:02.278 --> 00:31:03.780
What would you
call it. then?

508
00:31:06.157 --> 00:31:09.494
- I'm reading.
- While your mother waits?

509
00:31:13.206 --> 00:31:14.958
You're angry.

510
00:31:18.128 --> 00:31:19.212
Aren't you?

511
00:31:19.337 --> 00:31:20.839
I don't see what
good it would do.

512
00:31:22.132 --> 00:31:24.384
They are an insult to us.

513
00:31:24.509 --> 00:31:26.344
To what makes us
Targaryens.

514
00:31:26.469 --> 00:31:28.304
If any common lout
can ride a dragon.

515
00:31:28.346 --> 00:31:31.391
- then...
- That does not make me common. Or you.

516
00:31:32.559 --> 00:31:35.228
- You know what I am.
- I don't care.

517
00:31:35.353 --> 00:31:37.355
You are
the crown prince.

518
00:31:37.397 --> 00:31:39.149
the son of
the rightful queen.

519
00:31:39.190 --> 00:31:40.567
and here you are sulking

520
00:31:40.692 --> 00:31:42.294
because you believe that
if not for the dragon

521
00:31:42.318 --> 00:31:43.903
or the trappings
of your station.

522
00:31:44.029 --> 00:31:45.655
that you are nothing.

523
00:31:45.697 --> 00:31:48.324
(chuckles) Do you believe that you
are the first noble heir

524
00:31:48.366 --> 00:31:50.869
who was not sired
by his noble father?

525
00:31:51.369 --> 00:31:53.663
Such is the way
of the world. Jace.

526
00:31:53.705 --> 00:31:56.875
and in resenting it.
you only diminish yourself.

527
00:31:57.000 --> 00:31:58.501
Easy enough
to say.

528
00:31:58.877 --> 00:32:01.421
I've heard the whispers
the whole of my life.

529
00:32:01.546 --> 00:32:03.882
Then prove to them
that you are worthy.

530
00:32:03.923 --> 00:32:05.342
Get up
and take your place

531
00:32:05.383 --> 00:32:06.885
by your mother's side.

532
00:32:09.054 --> 00:32:12.432
(light. tense music playing)

533
00:32:17.729 --> 00:32:19.731
(wind blowing)

534
00:32:21.733 --> 00:32:23.401
(shivering)

535
00:32:25.111 --> 00:32:27.364
♪♪

536
00:32:31.242 --> 00:32:34.412
Tyland (singing halfheartedly):
♪ Here come my lads. my comely boys ♪

537
00:32:34.537 --> 00:32:36.873
♪ And split your sacks ashore ♪

538
00:32:36.915 --> 00:32:40.251
♪ For you'll be
sail-sailing many days ♪

539
00:32:40.293 --> 00:32:42.045
♪ Afore you get
some more ♪

540
00:32:42.587 --> 00:32:45.465
♪ So grease the mast
and send it up ♪

541
00:32:46.591 --> 00:32:48.927
♪ Betwixt the wind
and water ♪

542
00:32:49.469 --> 00:32:51.888
♪ Hoist. me lads.
and hoist again ♪

543
00:32:52.430 --> 00:32:55.767
♪ Salute the captain's
daughter ♪

544
00:33:00.105 --> 00:33:02.107
Well done.
Lord Tyrod!

545
00:33:10.615 --> 00:33:14.160
Good song.
well delivered.

546
00:33:14.285 --> 00:33:16.579
(indistinct chatter)

547
00:33:16.621 --> 00:33:18.957
(futilely)
It's Tyland.

548
00:33:20.458 --> 00:33:23.169
You have proven yourself
most accommodating.

549
00:33:23.294 --> 00:33:26.798
And more accomplished
than one would think. to look at you.

550
00:33:26.840 --> 00:33:29.843
Hm. Well... Hm.

551
00:33:31.970 --> 00:33:35.473
I will be pleased
to sail at your side.

552
00:33:37.183 --> 00:33:39.811
- Oh.
- And my captains with me.

553
00:33:45.358 --> 00:33:47.318
(chattering stops)

554
00:33:47.444 --> 00:33:50.280
To the Gullet
on the morrow!

555
00:33:50.321 --> 00:33:52.490
(all cheering)

556
00:33:56.661 --> 00:33:58.955
And let the Sea Snake

557
00:33:58.997 --> 00:34:01.332
rue the day
we meet again.

558
00:34:01.458 --> 00:34:03.835
(all cheering)

559
00:34:05.670 --> 00:34:08.130
Ya! My king will
be well pleased.

560
00:34:08.172 --> 00:34:09.799
To friendship!

561
00:34:09.841 --> 00:34:11.551
(cheering)

562
00:34:13.178 --> 00:34:16.139
(percussive music playing)

563
00:34:16.181 --> 00:34:18.016
(indistinct chatter)

564
00:34:24.188 --> 00:34:26.232
It is late.

565
00:34:26.358 --> 00:34:28.360
(Tyland clears throat)

566
00:34:28.902 --> 00:34:30.027
Oh!

567
00:34:30.362 --> 00:34:32.030
Before you go...

568
00:34:32.864 --> 00:34:33.989
Lord Tyland.

569
00:34:34.032 --> 00:34:35.033
Mm.

570
00:34:36.493 --> 00:34:37.911
You are
a handsome man.

571
00:34:38.036 --> 00:34:43.875
and you have proven
your worth and virility.

572
00:34:45.877 --> 00:34:48.045
I wish to have
children by you.

573
00:34:52.384 --> 00:34:56.054
(stammers) You. you...
You want me to...

574
00:34:56.096 --> 00:34:57.514
Indeed.

575
00:34:59.849 --> 00:35:02.060
I want you
to fuck my wives.

576
00:35:06.606 --> 00:35:10.026
How many wives
do you have?

577
00:35:13.571 --> 00:35:16.449
Ulf: (gulps)
More wine here!

578
00:35:17.867 --> 00:35:20.078
Taming a dragon
is thirsty work.

579
00:35:24.916 --> 00:35:27.752
Oh. and some more
of these little birds.

580
00:35:28.795 --> 00:35:30.130
(sighs)

581
00:35:34.592 --> 00:35:36.094
Rhaenyra:
A toast.

582
00:35:37.721 --> 00:35:40.098
To our new riders.

583
00:35:41.057 --> 00:35:43.268
The three of you
are not of noble birth.

584
00:35:43.309 --> 00:35:46.479
but you have done
a thing never dreamed of before now.

585
00:35:46.604 --> 00:35:49.441
- (Ulf chuckling)
- (Jacaerys sighs)

586
00:35:58.158 --> 00:36:01.661
I have entrusted you
with a power only few have known.

587
00:36:01.786 --> 00:36:05.457
And I charge you to take it up
with fealty and respect.

588
00:36:06.124 --> 00:36:10.253
Serve me well. and I will make you
knights of the realm.

589
00:36:10.295 --> 00:36:13.089
Huh? What do you think
of that. boys?

590
00:36:13.506 --> 00:36:16.009
We'll be knights...
just like that.

591
00:36:16.134 --> 00:36:18.470
We will not fail you.
my queen.

592
00:36:20.138 --> 00:36:21.848
What must we do?

593
00:36:24.142 --> 00:36:27.520
I had thought the mere fact of
you might stay the enemy's hand.

594
00:36:29.314 --> 00:36:31.107
But Lord Corlys
is right.

595
00:36:31.441 --> 00:36:35.278
We must strike while
we have the advantage...

596
00:36:35.320 --> 00:36:36.488
and end this war.

597
00:36:36.821 --> 00:36:39.491
Learn your beasts
and your commands.

598
00:36:39.949 --> 00:36:41.659
You will fly
in two days' time.

599
00:36:42.327 --> 00:36:45.997
The strongholds of the usurper.
Oldtown and Lannisport.

600
00:36:46.039 --> 00:36:49.793
and their armies.
all must be subdued.

601
00:36:50.377 --> 00:36:53.463
Alone. without allies.
he will have no choice but to surrender.

602
00:36:53.505 --> 00:36:55.799
You wish for us
to kill innocents.

603
00:36:55.840 --> 00:36:58.051
- And so many.
- Jacaerys Velaryon: It is hard...

604
00:36:59.135 --> 00:37:00.970
but it cannot
be helped.

605
00:37:01.012 --> 00:37:02.013
(Ulf grunts)

606
00:37:05.684 --> 00:37:07.977
We must break the will
of our enemy...

607
00:37:08.728 --> 00:37:10.188
or more will die
in a struggle

608
00:37:10.230 --> 00:37:11.564
that stretches
on without end.

609
00:37:11.690 --> 00:37:14.150
What about Vhagar?

610
00:37:14.192 --> 00:37:20.156
She is fearsome...
but she is one dragon.

611
00:37:20.198 --> 00:37:22.200
The prince regent cannot
defend against all of us.

612
00:37:22.242 --> 00:37:26.037
I'll take him on myself.
Silverwing's a goer. she is.

613
00:37:26.079 --> 00:37:28.498
- We're afraid of nothing.
- Addam of Hull: Hm.

614
00:37:28.873 --> 00:37:31.376
- Even if you are.
- There will be time enough

615
00:37:31.418 --> 00:37:33.169
to see which one
of us is a coward.

616
00:37:34.379 --> 00:37:36.881
I said more of
these little birds!

617
00:37:38.216 --> 00:37:42.595
A knight will comport himself
with grace at the queen's table.

618
00:37:42.929 --> 00:37:44.597
Best make me a knight. then.

619
00:37:48.727 --> 00:37:50.729
You forget yourself...

620
00:37:52.230 --> 00:37:53.606
friend.

621
00:37:55.442 --> 00:37:57.027
(scoffs)

622
00:37:57.736 --> 00:37:59.946
A sense of humor
would do you all good.

623
00:38:04.617 --> 00:38:06.369
(footsteps approach)

624
00:38:10.915 --> 00:38:14.210
(whispers) There is a message from Harrenhal.
Your Grace.

625
00:38:20.592 --> 00:38:21.718
Daemon?

626
00:38:21.760 --> 00:38:24.888
The castellan.
Ser Simon Strong.

627
00:38:24.929 --> 00:38:27.724
Daemon has raised
his army...

628
00:38:27.766 --> 00:38:30.977
- but Ser Simon fears treachery.
- (sighs)

629
00:38:34.272 --> 00:38:36.107
I will not allow it.

630
00:38:38.234 --> 00:38:39.235
Addam...

631
00:38:40.403 --> 00:38:41.780
come with me.

632
00:38:47.410 --> 00:38:48.787
Ulf: Thank you.

633
00:38:49.996 --> 00:38:50.997
Birds.

634
00:38:55.627 --> 00:38:57.796
(water dripping)

635
00:39:12.602 --> 00:39:14.813
Do you never sleep. witch?

636
00:39:19.609 --> 00:39:21.820
I'm goin'
to the godswood.

637
00:39:31.538 --> 00:39:33.790
(wind blowing)

638
00:39:47.971 --> 00:39:51.891
(antlered human shape
clip-clopping. grumbles)

639
00:39:52.017 --> 00:39:55.186
(eerie music playing)

640
00:39:59.232 --> 00:40:02.485
When you came here.
you were a closed fist.

641
00:40:04.863 --> 00:40:08.825
You wished to bend
the world to your will.

642
00:40:11.077 --> 00:40:13.830
But you've discovered.
I think. that...

643
00:40:13.872 --> 00:40:16.750
this world will
not be governed.

644
00:40:23.006 --> 00:40:26.551
There are omens here
for those who seek them.

645
00:40:29.888 --> 00:40:31.681
You do not scoff?

646
00:40:31.723 --> 00:40:35.226
- I'm no longer inclined to.
- (Alys chuckles)

647
00:40:36.394 --> 00:40:38.396
I'm pleased to hear it.

648
00:40:38.438 --> 00:40:40.440
♪♪

649
00:40:49.949 --> 00:40:53.745
Do you wish. then.
to learn what is given to you?

650
00:41:01.878 --> 00:41:03.797
All your life.
you have sought to command

651
00:41:03.922 --> 00:41:05.757
your own fate.

652
00:41:07.884 --> 00:41:09.969
(grabs Daemon's hand)

653
00:41:10.095 --> 00:41:12.389
But today you are ready.

654
00:41:12.430 --> 00:41:14.432
♪♪

655
00:41:29.614 --> 00:41:31.616
♪♪

656
00:41:31.658 --> 00:41:33.993
(bark crackling)

657
00:41:36.287 --> 00:41:38.289
(music intensifies)

658
00:41:38.331 --> 00:41:40.291
(crackling)

659
00:41:44.295 --> 00:41:46.256
(raven cawing)

660
00:41:46.297 --> 00:41:48.466
♪♪

661
00:41:49.801 --> 00:41:51.970
(soldiers fighting)

662
00:42:01.855 --> 00:42:03.440
(explosion booms)

663
00:42:04.149 --> 00:42:07.360
(light music playing)

664
00:42:07.485 --> 00:42:09.654
(dragon calls. screeches)

665
00:42:14.284 --> 00:42:16.286
♪♪

666
00:42:29.883 --> 00:42:33.136
(powerful music playing)

667
00:42:35.847 --> 00:42:39.017
Helaena (echoes):
It's all a story...

668
00:42:47.025 --> 00:42:49.986
and you are but
one part in it.

669
00:42:51.696 --> 00:42:53.823
You know your part.

670
00:42:53.865 --> 00:42:56.826
- (music fades out)
- (wind blowing)

671
00:42:56.868 --> 00:42:59.079
(bark crackling)

672
00:43:03.875 --> 00:43:06.419
You know what you must do.

673
00:43:06.878 --> 00:43:08.546
(footsteps approach)

674
00:43:14.928 --> 00:43:16.846
Sister.

675
00:43:16.888 --> 00:43:18.848
We share
the same blood.

676
00:43:18.890 --> 00:43:20.934
you and I.

677
00:43:21.059 --> 00:43:24.062
I know you wish
no harm to anyone.

678
00:43:26.106 --> 00:43:28.358
But in a time
like this.

679
00:43:28.400 --> 00:43:31.361
when the good
of the realm depends on us...

680
00:43:34.239 --> 00:43:37.242
Our mother is not
a dragonrider.

681
00:43:37.701 --> 00:43:39.411
She cannot understand

682
00:43:39.452 --> 00:43:42.706
that you and I have
a truer call to heed.

683
00:43:47.460 --> 00:43:49.212
Come with me...

684
00:43:50.380 --> 00:43:51.715
to Harrenhal?

685
00:43:53.550 --> 00:43:56.761
We will lay waste
to Daemon and his army.

686
00:43:57.429 --> 00:44:02.600
Let our enemy see that we will answer
outrage with outrage.

687
00:44:02.726 --> 00:44:04.728
And if I refuse?

688
00:44:07.439 --> 00:44:10.400
Will you burn me
as you did Aegon?

689
00:44:14.237 --> 00:44:17.115
- That is a lie.
- I saw it.

690
00:44:20.452 --> 00:44:24.497
You burned him
and you let him fall.

691
00:44:28.501 --> 00:44:30.503
What you say is treason.

692
00:44:32.839 --> 00:44:35.425
Aegon will be king again.

693
00:44:38.303 --> 00:44:40.972
He's yet to see victory.

694
00:44:41.848 --> 00:44:44.601
He sits on
a wooden throne.

695
00:44:45.352 --> 00:44:46.686
And you...

696
00:44:51.149 --> 00:44:53.318
(whispers)
you'll be dead.

697
00:44:55.653 --> 00:44:58.698
You were swallowed up
in the God's Eye.

698
00:44:58.823 --> 00:45:00.658
and you were
never seen again.

699
00:45:02.827 --> 00:45:05.955
(light. tense music playing)

700
00:45:05.997 --> 00:45:08.667
(whispers)
I could have you killed.

701
00:45:09.376 --> 00:45:12.337
(softly) It wouldn't
change anything.

702
00:45:13.380 --> 00:45:15.382
♪♪

703
00:45:24.140 --> 00:45:27.519
- (intense music playing)
- (Syrax roars)

704
00:45:27.852 --> 00:45:30.021
(Seasmoke roars)

705
00:45:32.899 --> 00:45:35.151
(Caraxes grumbles)

706
00:45:38.029 --> 00:45:39.531
(roars)

707
00:45:49.499 --> 00:45:51.918
♪♪

708
00:45:52.043 --> 00:45:54.212
(all yelling)

709
00:45:57.716 --> 00:46:00.260
(singers vocalizing)

710
00:46:02.762 --> 00:46:04.764
(dragons calling)

711
00:46:14.607 --> 00:46:16.359
(screeches)

712
00:46:22.407 --> 00:46:23.783
(roars)

713
00:46:27.078 --> 00:46:29.247
♪♪

714
00:46:32.584 --> 00:46:35.754
I am the castellan.
Ser Simon Strong. Your Grace.

715
00:46:35.879 --> 00:46:37.922
Well met.

716
00:46:38.048 --> 00:46:39.966
Welcome to Harrenhal.
my queen.

717
00:46:40.091 --> 00:46:41.569
I did not think
to see you here yourself.

718
00:46:41.593 --> 00:46:44.554
(exhales) Your message
gave me much concern.

719
00:46:44.596 --> 00:46:47.432
Yes. I must admit
I had reason to fear.

720
00:46:49.267 --> 00:46:51.227
But come.
see for yourself.

721
00:46:55.273 --> 00:46:57.442
(Seasmoke calls)

722
00:47:01.446 --> 00:47:03.615
(indistinct chatter)

723
00:47:19.964 --> 00:47:21.925
(chatter quiets)

724
00:47:21.966 --> 00:47:24.427
(Syrax screeching)

725
00:47:25.970 --> 00:47:27.514
(roars)

726
00:47:32.811 --> 00:47:34.270
(silence)

727
00:47:34.312 --> 00:47:37.482
(light. tense music playing)

728
00:48:06.970 --> 00:48:08.972
♪♪

729
00:48:21.192 --> 00:48:23.737
I wasn't
expecting you.

730
00:48:26.197 --> 00:48:28.533
That seems rather
a lapse in foresight.

731
00:48:31.536 --> 00:48:34.706
- I see you have done well here.
- They are sworn to me.

732
00:48:35.373 --> 00:48:37.667
And not a moment
too soon.

733
00:48:42.380 --> 00:48:44.716
And to whom
are you sworn?

734
00:49:00.899 --> 00:49:02.901
(speaking High Valyrian)

735
00:49:19.918 --> 00:49:22.629
(speaking High Valyrian)

736
00:49:42.273 --> 00:49:44.442
The realm's only hope...

737
00:49:44.943 --> 00:49:46.444
is a leader
who can unite it

738
00:49:46.486 --> 00:49:50.073
and my brother
chose... you.

739
00:49:53.118 --> 00:49:56.329
(light music playing)

740
00:50:09.175 --> 00:50:11.636
You are the true queen.
Rhaenyra.

741
00:50:12.429 --> 00:50:14.472
First of Her Name.

742
00:50:14.848 --> 00:50:16.850
Protector of the Realm.

743
00:50:17.434 --> 00:50:21.271
I am meant to serve you.
and all of these with me.

744
00:50:21.354 --> 00:50:23.273
until death

745
00:50:23.314 --> 00:50:25.859
or the end of our story.

746
00:50:30.280 --> 00:50:33.450
(music intensifies)

747
00:50:51.509 --> 00:50:53.803
(music softens)

748
00:50:58.308 --> 00:51:00.518
(speaking High Valyrian)

749
00:51:08.234 --> 00:51:10.487
(speaking High Valyrian)

750
00:51:15.367 --> 00:51:17.077
My queen.

751
00:51:26.878 --> 00:51:30.340
(shouting) For every one of us
who falls...

752
00:51:30.382 --> 00:51:32.550
a hundred of them!

753
00:51:32.676 --> 00:51:35.887
There will be
no mercy!

754
00:51:36.221 --> 00:51:38.556
We fight for our queen!

755
00:51:38.890 --> 00:51:40.392
(all cheering)

756
00:51:40.433 --> 00:51:43.687
(heroic music playing)

757
00:51:47.565 --> 00:51:49.734
(Daemon shouting)

758
00:51:51.736 --> 00:51:53.738
♪♪

759
00:52:04.082 --> 00:52:06.292
(music softens)

760
00:52:06.418 --> 00:52:08.086
(cranking)

761
00:52:09.421 --> 00:52:11.589
(indistinct chatter)

762
00:52:19.097 --> 00:52:21.099
(seagulls cawing)

763
00:52:23.768 --> 00:52:26.104
You sent for me.
Lord Hand.

764
00:52:27.772 --> 00:52:30.734
Gulls are flying
low today.

765
00:52:30.775 --> 00:52:32.777
The weather
will change.

766
00:52:33.445 --> 00:52:35.780
Not until late.
I think. but...

767
00:52:35.905 --> 00:52:38.158
- I will ready the storm sails.
- We join the blockade.

768
00:52:38.283 --> 00:52:42.787
and are like to find ourselves in peril.
sooner than late.

769
00:52:43.747 --> 00:52:47.292
I wish to set out on good terms
with my first mate.

770
00:52:47.792 --> 00:52:49.502
Have I been remiss
in my duties?

771
00:52:49.627 --> 00:52:52.922
You've done what
is asked of you. and more.

772
00:52:52.964 --> 00:52:56.634
But you are curt...
silent.

773
00:52:56.676 --> 00:52:59.929
and the men
find you distant.

774
00:53:00.472 --> 00:53:02.932
You cannot lead
if you do not inspire.

775
00:53:03.308 --> 00:53:06.144
Well. I never asked to lead.
as you well know.

776
00:53:08.813 --> 00:53:12.108
You have been given a position to
which all who serve here aspire.

777
00:53:14.486 --> 00:53:16.488
Forgive me. my lord.

778
00:53:16.613 --> 00:53:18.990
I will endeavor
to improve myself.

779
00:53:19.657 --> 00:53:21.826
(birds cawing)

780
00:53:22.827 --> 00:53:25.622
(softly)
I am trying to help you.

781
00:53:31.836 --> 00:53:33.630
You want
to help me?

782
00:53:35.173 --> 00:53:37.509
Is this the help
you offer after all these years?

783
00:53:37.550 --> 00:53:40.011
A reminder
to be grateful?

784
00:53:40.679 --> 00:53:42.180
I mean no offense.

785
00:53:43.014 --> 00:53:44.182
You may go.

786
00:53:47.686 --> 00:53:50.063
Do you know what
it was like for us?

787
00:53:51.356 --> 00:53:53.483
To grow up
fatherless...

788
00:53:53.525 --> 00:53:55.485
to be sneered upon
as bastards.

789
00:53:55.527 --> 00:53:57.153
never sure
of the bread to feed us?

790
00:53:57.237 --> 00:53:59.989
D-D-Do you know
what hunger does to a boy?

791
00:54:01.032 --> 00:54:02.534
What grief does?

792
00:54:03.034 --> 00:54:05.578
- Or shame?
- You are dismissed.

793
00:54:05.912 --> 00:54:08.206
I sold fish
in the market

794
00:54:08.331 --> 00:54:10.875
from cold dawn
until sunset.

795
00:54:10.917 --> 00:54:13.503
putting by coppers
to stave off the winter.

796
00:54:13.545 --> 00:54:16.548
and I watched the man
who sired me walk past

797
00:54:16.589 --> 00:54:19.426
with his son and heir

798
00:54:19.551 --> 00:54:22.512
with a fur
around his shoulders...

799
00:54:22.929 --> 00:54:28.184
choosing sweetmeats
to eat after supper by the fire.

800
00:54:30.228 --> 00:54:32.397
And now that boy is dead.

801
00:54:32.522 --> 00:54:34.441
And his sister before him.

802
00:54:34.566 --> 00:54:36.026
And the heir
that took his place.

803
00:54:36.067 --> 00:54:40.030
And now. now. now
you remember I live.

804
00:54:41.406 --> 00:54:43.199
Now you wish to...

805
00:54:43.241 --> 00:54:46.202
suddenly to scatter
the crumbs of your favor.

806
00:54:48.413 --> 00:54:52.792
I am an honorable man.
and I will serve you because I must.

807
00:54:53.293 --> 00:54:56.046
But if it is
all the same.

808
00:54:56.087 --> 00:55:00.800
I will decline
any offers of help.

809
00:55:02.719 --> 00:55:04.721
If I survive
this war...

810
00:55:04.971 --> 00:55:07.766
I will continue
as I began...

811
00:55:09.434 --> 00:55:10.769
alone.

812
00:55:15.148 --> 00:55:18.151
(solemn music playing)

813
00:55:34.459 --> 00:55:36.169
(panting)

814
00:55:38.838 --> 00:55:41.675
- (dragon calls)
- (gasps)

815
00:55:41.800 --> 00:55:45.136
(tense. exciting music playing)

816
00:55:48.807 --> 00:55:50.975
(dragon calls)

817
00:55:58.191 --> 00:56:01.528
(music fades out)

818
00:56:01.653 --> 00:56:05.365
Mysaria: You have done
what no one else would dream of.

819
00:56:05.490 --> 00:56:08.326
and you have
been rewarded.

820
00:56:08.368 --> 00:56:10.620
The gods
favor you.

821
00:56:11.329 --> 00:56:14.499
They put the means to victory
in your hands.

822
00:56:14.541 --> 00:56:18.670
And yet. to claim it.
I must strike

823
00:56:18.712 --> 00:56:22.215
and in striking.
I doom thousands to their deaths.

824
00:56:22.340 --> 00:56:24.342
(dragons grumbling)

825
00:56:27.012 --> 00:56:30.348
I do not believe
my father would've wished this.

826
00:56:30.390 --> 00:56:32.517
He left you
with no choice.

827
00:56:32.642 --> 00:56:36.062
Be strong.
You know you are just.

828
00:56:36.187 --> 00:56:37.981
You must not let
the Realm fall to those

829
00:56:38.023 --> 00:56:40.900
who care for power
more than peace.

830
00:56:41.317 --> 00:56:43.528
You must prevail.

831
00:56:46.531 --> 00:56:48.533
And who pays the price?

832
00:56:52.871 --> 00:56:56.082
(dragons grumbling. screeching)

833
00:57:01.713 --> 00:57:03.381
(bangs on door)

834
00:57:06.551 --> 00:57:07.677
Come.

835
00:57:07.719 --> 00:57:09.888
(door opens)

836
00:57:12.098 --> 00:57:14.351
Begging your pardon.
Your Grace.

837
00:57:27.697 --> 00:57:29.908
I had to see you.

838
00:57:38.583 --> 00:57:40.210
- Who knows?
- None save my protector.

839
00:57:40.251 --> 00:57:42.796
He laid down his sword
at your gate.

840
00:57:45.423 --> 00:57:46.966
(sighs)

841
00:57:52.222 --> 00:57:56.768
I've been. I think...
mistaken.

842
00:57:58.603 --> 00:57:59.771
In what?

843
00:58:00.605 --> 00:58:03.733
I was raised to believe there was
an order to things.

844
00:58:03.817 --> 00:58:08.446
that there was security
in following the paths laid out for us.

845
00:58:09.114 --> 00:58:10.281
I resented you.
I think.

846
00:58:10.323 --> 00:58:12.659
for... caring so little
for any of it.

847
00:58:12.784 --> 00:58:15.453
for knowing
what you wanted.

848
00:58:15.954 --> 00:58:17.956
I did not know
what I wanted.

849
00:58:18.331 --> 00:58:20.959
I knew only what
was expected of me.

850
00:58:23.962 --> 00:58:27.090
- Why have you come here?
- Because I lost my way.

851
00:58:27.132 --> 00:58:29.801
Or rather.
it was taken from me.

852
00:58:30.176 --> 00:58:32.262
All those I put
my faith in. my...

853
00:58:32.303 --> 00:58:35.348
- m-my husband. my father. my lover. my son...
- Ooh.

854
00:58:35.473 --> 00:58:37.017
The incorruptible queen

855
00:58:37.142 --> 00:58:38.476
sullies herself
with a lover.

856
00:58:38.518 --> 00:58:40.812
Do not judge me
for what you yourself have done.

857
00:58:41.312 --> 00:58:44.024
Your father died.
I took comfort with another.

858
00:58:44.524 --> 00:58:48.194
- I too have desires.
- Yes. but you alone made virtue your banner.

859
00:58:48.319 --> 00:58:51.489
And I clung to it...
in defiance of you.

860
00:58:51.614 --> 00:58:54.325
I think. who
so disdained it.

861
00:59:05.003 --> 00:59:07.172
I have been
alone. of late.

862
00:59:07.213 --> 00:59:09.341
I walked outside
the walls of the city

863
00:59:09.466 --> 00:59:11.718
and I felt a weight
lifted from me.

864
00:59:12.010 --> 00:59:14.679
- How lovely for you.
- I thought. for the first time.

865
00:59:14.721 --> 00:59:16.723
what I would choose...

866
00:59:17.182 --> 00:59:19.059
if not for the duty
I put before all else.

867
00:59:19.184 --> 00:59:22.979
(chuckles) Shall you cast
your son down and rule alone?

868
00:59:23.021 --> 00:59:25.732
No. I do not wish to rule.
I wish to live.

869
00:59:26.191 --> 00:59:29.652
To be free of all this
endless plotting and striving.

870
00:59:29.694 --> 00:59:31.988
The crown will pursue war
and victory at any cost.

871
00:59:32.030 --> 00:59:36.701
I... (sniffles)
But as for me...

872
00:59:36.826 --> 00:59:40.872
I would take my daughter
and her child and leave it all behind.

873
00:59:41.915 --> 00:59:45.669
(chuckles)
It's too late... Alicent.

874
00:59:46.878 --> 00:59:49.673
You said it yourself.
Blood has been shed.

875
00:59:49.714 --> 00:59:51.675
cities burned.
armies march.

876
00:59:51.716 --> 00:59:53.677
and you wish
to wash your hands

877
00:59:53.718 --> 00:59:55.220
of what you yourself
set in motion.

878
00:59:55.261 --> 00:59:56.930
Oh. the arrogance
of blaming me.

879
00:59:57.055 --> 00:59:58.574
as if you would not
have been challenged regardless.

880
00:59:58.598 --> 01:00:00.558
Did not your hand
bring it forth like a midwife?

881
01:00:00.684 --> 01:00:03.395
I did only what
I thought your father wanted.

882
01:00:05.563 --> 01:00:07.232
Oh. go then.

883
01:00:08.233 --> 01:00:09.734
Leave us behind.
as you say.

884
01:00:09.859 --> 01:00:11.403
(scoffs)
Rhaenyra.

885
01:00:12.070 --> 01:00:14.739
- Wander in the wilderness.
- (Alicent sighs)

886
01:00:14.781 --> 01:00:17.033
What has it got
to do with me?

887
01:00:21.079 --> 01:00:24.249
Did you come here
thinking you would be absolved?

888
01:00:29.921 --> 01:00:31.423
(sighs)

889
01:00:43.143 --> 01:00:45.895
He never stopped loving your mother.
you know?

890
01:00:46.438 --> 01:00:48.398
He was very fond of me.
and I of him.

891
01:00:48.440 --> 01:00:49.607
but...

892
01:00:50.442 --> 01:00:52.944
she was the vision
that sustained him

893
01:00:53.737 --> 01:00:54.821
even after
she herself

894
01:00:54.946 --> 01:00:57.157
had slipped
from his grasp. it was

895
01:00:57.282 --> 01:00:58.992
his love for her
that kept him resolute

896
01:00:59.117 --> 01:01:00.910
in his choice
of heir.

897
01:01:00.952 --> 01:01:03.455
And yet. you believe
he wavered at the end.

898
01:01:09.794 --> 01:01:12.005
Why have you come here?

899
01:01:12.505 --> 01:01:13.840
(sniffles)

900
01:01:14.466 --> 01:01:17.635
Aemond will soon fly to join Cole
in the Riverlands.

901
01:01:18.595 --> 01:01:19.846
(deep breath)

902
01:01:19.971 --> 01:01:21.473
When he's gone...

903
01:01:21.973 --> 01:01:24.100
Helaena as queen will be
the crown's authority.

904
01:01:24.142 --> 01:01:26.269
If you come then to King's Landing.
I will see to it

905
01:01:26.311 --> 01:01:28.104
that our guards
throw down their arms.

906
01:01:28.146 --> 01:01:31.316
we will open the gates.
we will shed no blood.

907
01:01:31.983 --> 01:01:34.694
- You will enter as a conqueror.
- (laughs)

908
01:01:35.945 --> 01:01:38.156
Already you have
the stronger hand.

909
01:01:38.990 --> 01:01:40.325
Once you take the throne...

910
01:01:40.367 --> 01:01:44.162
(deep breath)
this senseless war must end.

911
01:01:46.664 --> 01:01:48.166
(softly)
Right.

912
01:01:52.170 --> 01:01:53.505
What of Aegon?

913
01:02:00.845 --> 01:02:04.182
He's broken
beyond recognition.

914
01:02:05.392 --> 01:02:08.645
He lies in the dark.
in pain and terror.

915
01:02:09.020 --> 01:02:10.689
He has many faults.
but...

916
01:02:11.690 --> 01:02:12.857
he still heeds his mother.

917
01:02:12.899 --> 01:02:14.192
I believe I can
prevail upon him

918
01:02:14.317 --> 01:02:17.654
- to bend the knee. if indeed...
- No! Still...

919
01:02:17.696 --> 01:02:19.364
you defend him.

920
01:02:21.032 --> 01:02:24.202
Still you imagine you
can have all you want

921
01:02:24.327 --> 01:02:25.662
without paying
too high a price.

922
01:02:25.704 --> 01:02:28.039
- a price I had no choice but to pay.
- What I want

923
01:02:28.081 --> 01:02:30.333
is to set things right.

924
01:02:32.168 --> 01:02:34.004
If I am to take
the throne.

925
01:02:34.045 --> 01:02:37.215
I must put an end
to the opposition.

926
01:02:37.340 --> 01:02:38.842
I must take
Aegon's head.

927
01:02:38.883 --> 01:02:40.719
And I have to do it
for all to see.

928
01:02:40.844 --> 01:02:42.554
You know this.

929
01:02:44.097 --> 01:02:47.183
However you may try to evade it.
you know this.

930
01:02:57.902 --> 01:02:59.237
Choose.

931
01:03:00.071 --> 01:03:02.240
(deep breath)

932
01:03:08.413 --> 01:03:11.249
Will you shrink from what
you set out to do?

933
01:03:11.374 --> 01:03:13.585
Or will you
see it through...

934
01:03:14.753 --> 01:03:16.546
and make your sacrifice?

935
01:03:21.593 --> 01:03:23.595
A son for a son.

936
01:03:42.113 --> 01:03:43.615
(exhales)

937
01:03:46.743 --> 01:03:48.286
(sniffles)

938
01:03:55.627 --> 01:03:56.795
(sighs)

939
01:04:00.840 --> 01:04:02.842
(deep breath)

940
01:04:04.010 --> 01:04:06.429
(both crying softly)

941
01:04:16.773 --> 01:04:18.525
You are much changed.

942
01:04:18.983 --> 01:04:22.529
(sniffling) Let us be done
with this. please.

943
01:04:24.656 --> 01:04:27.325
And what do I do
with you now?

944
01:04:28.993 --> 01:04:33.665
You let me go.
to do what I promised.

945
01:04:33.707 --> 01:04:36.126
And you fly to the Red Keep
in three days' time.

946
01:04:36.167 --> 01:04:38.211
and you take
your throne.

947
01:04:38.336 --> 01:04:41.339
Or you take me
for a liar.

948
01:04:41.464 --> 01:04:42.841
I have neither
weapon nor armor.

949
01:04:42.966 --> 01:04:44.134
My life itself
is forfeit.

950
01:04:44.175 --> 01:04:47.220
I... cast myself
on the mercy of a friend

951
01:04:47.345 --> 01:04:49.514
who once loved me.

952
01:04:51.182 --> 01:04:52.892
History will paint
you a villain.

953
01:04:57.188 --> 01:04:59.357
A cold queen...

954
01:05:01.693 --> 01:05:04.529
grasping for power.
and then defeated.

955
01:05:05.071 --> 01:05:07.323
Let them think
what they must.

956
01:05:09.534 --> 01:05:11.703
I am at last myself...

957
01:05:12.412 --> 01:05:17.542
with no ambition greater than to walk
where I please and to breathe the open air.

958
01:05:19.836 --> 01:05:22.714
To die unremarked
and unnoticed...

959
01:05:24.215 --> 01:05:25.884
and be free.

960
01:05:29.554 --> 01:05:32.223
You speak as if
from a distant dream.

961
01:05:33.058 --> 01:05:34.559
Come with me.

962
01:05:38.396 --> 01:05:42.567
My part is here.
whether I will or no.

963
01:05:43.443 --> 01:05:46.404
It was decided
for me long ago.

964
01:05:52.744 --> 01:05:54.621
(softly)
Go.

965
01:05:59.250 --> 01:06:02.420
(melancholy music playing)

966
01:06:20.438 --> 01:06:22.565
(music intensifies)

967
01:06:52.762 --> 01:06:54.472
(panting)

968
01:06:54.973 --> 01:06:56.975
♪♪

969
01:07:01.479 --> 01:07:04.816
(tense. anticipatory
music playing)

970
01:07:18.705 --> 01:07:20.999
(roars)

971
01:07:29.049 --> 01:07:31.051
♪♪

972
01:07:50.904 --> 01:07:52.906
♪♪

973
01:08:07.504 --> 01:08:09.714
♪♪

974
01:08:27.899 --> 01:08:29.901
♪♪

975
01:09:00.890 --> 01:09:02.892
♪♪

976
01:09:10.774 --> 01:09:12.569
(panting)

977
01:09:17.115 --> 01:09:19.117
(dragon grumbles)

978
01:09:23.287 --> 01:09:24.663
(roars)

979
01:09:25.415 --> 01:09:27.625
♪♪

980
01:09:39.679 --> 01:09:42.265
(singers vocalizing)

981
01:10:00.325 --> 01:10:02.535
(animals chattering)

982
01:10:07.499 --> 01:10:09.376
♪♪

983
01:10:09.501 --> 01:10:11.670
(vocalizing continues)

984
01:10:32.649 --> 01:10:35.193
(music. vocalizing fades out)

985
01:10:38.863 --> 01:10:42.033
(intense music playing)

986
01:11:12.522 --> 01:11:14.733
♪♪

987
01:11:31.583 --> 01:11:34.085
(singers vocalizing)

988
01:11:45.638 --> 01:11:47.974
(music. vocalizing fades out)

989
01:11:55.273 --> 01:11:56.649
♪ (THRILLING MUSIC PLAYS)

990
01:11:56.900 --> 01:11:59.110
RYAN CONDAL: The final episode
is such a great build

991
01:11:59.152 --> 01:12:00.672
for everywhere we've been
in season two

992
01:12:00.779 --> 01:12:02.280
and promising what's to come.

993
01:12:04.324 --> 01:12:06.159
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYS)

994
01:12:07.786 --> 01:12:08.953
(CROWD CLAMORING)

995
01:12:09.287 --> 01:12:12.665
SARA HESS: Rhaenyra has choked
King's Landing with a blockade.

996
01:12:12.791 --> 01:12:14.101
and people are starting
to get hungry.

997
01:12:14.125 --> 01:12:16.252
and they're going to revolt
against the King.

998
01:12:16.294 --> 01:12:17.337
or the Prince Regent.

999
01:12:17.754 --> 01:12:20.090
Break the blockade.
and it will benefit you.

1000
01:12:20.173 --> 01:12:23.635
It seems you need us
more than we need you.

1001
01:12:24.094 --> 01:12:26.971
There is a Lannister navy.
there is a Hightower navy.

1002
01:12:27.097 --> 01:12:29.307
but they're on the other side
of the blockade.

1003
01:12:29.432 --> 01:12:32.018
And so they end up going
to bargain with the Triarchy

1004
01:12:32.352 --> 01:12:35.522
which Tyland is very
not on board with.

1005
01:12:35.605 --> 01:12:36.856
but ends up having to do.

1006
01:12:36.981 --> 01:12:40.110
But it's a sign of how extreme
their position is.

1007
01:12:40.318 --> 01:12:41.921
RYAN: This is where
the seat of power sits.

1008
01:12:41.945 --> 01:12:45.115
And this is a very rich cartel
of three different nations

1009
01:12:45.156 --> 01:12:48.034
that are in the shipping
and piracy business.

1010
01:12:48.201 --> 01:12:49.661
And they hate Westeros.

1011
01:12:49.703 --> 01:12:52.163
And they want to seek a profit
off of them.

1012
01:12:52.664 --> 01:12:54.374
He gets sent to pirate land

1013
01:12:54.958 --> 01:12:56.167
to treat with the pirates.

1014
01:12:56.209 --> 01:12:58.503
To see if he can get
the Triarchy

1015
01:12:58.545 --> 01:13:00.380
to ally with the Greens.

1016
01:13:01.131 --> 01:13:02.131
Admiral Lohar.

1017
01:13:02.716 --> 01:13:05.477
ABIGAIL THORNE: He needs to impress me
before he can get what he wants.

1018
01:13:05.802 --> 01:13:08.013
I put him through absolute hell.

1019
01:13:08.054 --> 01:13:09.806
- (GROANING)
- (CROWD CHEERS)

1020
01:13:09.848 --> 01:13:10.849
Singing was the worst.

1021
01:13:11.224 --> 01:13:13.304
I can handle mud wrestling.
but singing is miserable.

1022
01:13:13.643 --> 01:13:15.562
But it worked
because Tyland can't sing.

1023
01:13:15.854 --> 01:13:17.731
RYAN: She's a bonkers character

1024
01:13:17.856 --> 01:13:20.025
that feels like one of these
very colorful characters

1025
01:13:20.066 --> 01:13:22.068
ripped right out of the pages
of George's books.

1026
01:13:22.235 --> 01:13:24.070
The people there take her
entirely seriously.

1027
01:13:24.154 --> 01:13:26.173
and we're sort of looking at her
the way Tyland does.

1028
01:13:26.197 --> 01:13:28.366
which is. "What's going on?"
and "Is this real?"

1029
01:13:28.533 --> 01:13:32.370
SARA: One of our season highlights
was bringing in Sharako Lohar.

1030
01:13:32.412 --> 01:13:34.164
And it can be a rough show.

1031
01:13:34.205 --> 01:13:37.083
It's grim. it's a war.
a lot of people die.

1032
01:13:37.208 --> 01:13:41.046
So having that moment of levity
and just sort of off-kilterness

1033
01:13:41.087 --> 01:13:42.714
was really important to us

1034
01:13:42.756 --> 01:13:45.592
and a really welcome
little bit of fun.

1035
01:13:45.675 --> 01:13:47.886
- (CROWD LAUGHS)
- A jest. my Lord.

1036
01:13:51.765 --> 01:13:53.405
RHAENYRA TARGARYEN:
How goes the Seasnake?

1037
01:13:53.600 --> 01:13:55.018
I've given her a new name.

1038
01:13:55.560 --> 01:13:56.936
The Queen Who Never Was.

1039
01:13:57.228 --> 01:13:59.564
We really wanted to find a way
for him to honor

1040
01:13:59.606 --> 01:14:01.358
and keep alive the memory
of Rhaenys.

1041
01:14:01.399 --> 01:14:03.276
Because it shows the arc
that he's been on

1042
01:14:03.401 --> 01:14:05.695
across the season
where much of his life

1043
01:14:05.737 --> 01:14:07.113
was about him
and his own glory.

1044
01:14:07.197 --> 01:14:09.240
I mean. he named his ship
after himself.

1045
01:14:09.574 --> 01:14:11.951
GEETA VASANT PATEL:
Corlys always went out to sea.

1046
01:14:12.077 --> 01:14:14.913
so Rhaenys never felt like
his priority.

1047
01:14:15.038 --> 01:14:19.250
And when she died.
it finally came to Corlys

1048
01:14:19.292 --> 01:14:21.211
that he always thought
about himself.

1049
01:14:21.294 --> 01:14:23.922
And so he did the one thing
he could do.

1050
01:14:23.963 --> 01:14:27.258
Take his namesake. his ship.
and make it hers.

1051
01:14:27.967 --> 01:14:30.136
SARA: He's lost all the people
he loves.

1052
01:14:30.303 --> 01:14:33.640
He's sort of come to this place
of acceptance

1053
01:14:33.765 --> 01:14:36.976
and understanding
that his great exploits

1054
01:14:37.102 --> 01:14:40.814
are less important than just
having his family around him.

1055
01:14:41.147 --> 01:14:43.066
Do you know what hunger does
to a boy?

1056
01:14:44.651 --> 01:14:45.652
What grief does?

1057
01:14:46.111 --> 01:14:49.322
Rhaenys always had
the conversation with Corlys

1058
01:14:49.406 --> 01:14:50.490
about his heir.

1059
01:14:50.657 --> 01:14:54.327
And none of them really feel
like they're the right person.

1060
01:14:54.452 --> 01:14:57.831
For the first time.
Corlys considers Addam and Alyn.

1061
01:14:58.123 --> 01:15:00.834
Yes. they are bastards.
but they are more qualified.

1062
01:15:01.167 --> 01:15:02.979
STEVE TOUSSAINT: One of
the things that we talked about.

1063
01:15:03.003 --> 01:15:04.963
myself. Abu. and Geeta.

1064
01:15:05.088 --> 01:15:08.133
was that nobody speaks
to Corlys that way.

1065
01:15:08.174 --> 01:15:09.467
Not if they've got any sense.

1066
01:15:09.801 --> 01:15:11.678
The only person who does
is Rhaenys.

1067
01:15:12.012 --> 01:15:14.973
When it came to the tirade.
this emotional speech.

1068
01:15:15.015 --> 01:15:16.683
it came down to the words

1069
01:15:16.808 --> 01:15:18.435
and playing off Steve
and his reactions.

1070
01:15:18.518 --> 01:15:21.312
Alyn doesn't expect it
coming out of him.

1071
01:15:21.479 --> 01:15:23.279
I wasn't expecting it
coming out of me either.

1072
01:15:23.314 --> 01:15:24.983
Like. it was one
of those moments

1073
01:15:25.025 --> 01:15:27.694
where I generally felt like
I could really let go.

1074
01:15:27.986 --> 01:15:29.863
I am trying to help you.

1075
01:15:30.155 --> 01:15:32.323
Now you remember I live.

1076
01:15:33.366 --> 01:15:35.201
STEVE: He watched me
with my other son.

1077
01:15:35.326 --> 01:15:37.871
picking up wonderful gifts
and walking into the castle.

1078
01:15:37.996 --> 01:15:40.206
And he.
who knew I was his father.

1079
01:15:40.540 --> 01:15:41.833
had to grow up in poverty.

1080
01:15:41.958 --> 01:15:43.686
For me then to come
into his life and sort of go.

1081
01:15:43.710 --> 01:15:44.794
"I'm trying to help you."

1082
01:15:44.878 --> 01:15:46.355
well. of course.
he's gonna be resentful.

1083
01:15:46.379 --> 01:15:48.579
You understand the hurt
and everything that he's carried

1084
01:15:48.673 --> 01:15:49.841
for all of these years.

1085
01:15:50.175 --> 01:15:52.010
You see the way it lands
on the Seasnake.

1086
01:15:52.177 --> 01:15:53.970
And I think he knows
that he hasn't been

1087
01:15:54.346 --> 01:15:55.823
the patriarchal figure
that he needed to be

1088
01:15:55.847 --> 01:15:56.847
to these guys.

1089
01:15:57.057 --> 01:15:58.784
but I don't think he realizes
until this moment

1090
01:15:58.808 --> 01:16:01.519
the cost that it had
on this human being.

1091
01:16:01.728 --> 01:16:03.355
If it is all the same.

1092
01:16:03.855 --> 01:16:07.901
I will decline any offers
of help.

1093
01:16:12.489 --> 01:16:14.908
(VHAGAR GROWLS. BELLOWS)

1094
01:16:15.033 --> 01:16:16.201
RYAN: Aemond lashes out.

1095
01:16:16.242 --> 01:16:18.912
It's also a strategic act
because Sharp Point

1096
01:16:19.037 --> 01:16:20.205
is the seat of House Massey

1097
01:16:20.246 --> 01:16:21.539
who serves
on Rhaenyra's council.

1098
01:16:21.664 --> 01:16:24.668
It's a punishment to them
for siding with the pretender.

1099
01:16:24.918 --> 01:16:26.478
Aemond is showing
that he's not running.

1100
01:16:26.544 --> 01:16:29.422
He's burning cities filled
with innocent people instead.

1101
01:16:30.215 --> 01:16:32.926
SARA: Aemond is now.
for the first time this season.

1102
01:16:33.051 --> 01:16:34.094
I think. scared.

1103
01:16:34.427 --> 01:16:37.764
From the time in season one
when he got Vhagar as a boy.

1104
01:16:37.847 --> 01:16:39.516
that's changed
his entire outlook.

1105
01:16:39.557 --> 01:16:42.185
And now that he's been
challenged by these new dragons.

1106
01:16:42.227 --> 01:16:43.467
it's the first time that. like.

1107
01:16:43.520 --> 01:16:45.605
"Oh. no. I don't have
the upper hand

1108
01:16:45.689 --> 01:16:47.607
in any situation I go into."

1109
01:16:47.941 --> 01:16:49.109
GEETA:
The stakes are so high

1110
01:16:49.275 --> 01:16:52.112
that if he doesn't get
another rider.

1111
01:16:52.237 --> 01:16:54.698
he will have no chance
against the Blacks.

1112
01:16:54.906 --> 01:16:59.119
And they will lose the throne
is Aegon continues to be king.

1113
01:16:59.452 --> 01:17:01.913
In his mind.
he's doing what's right

1114
01:17:01.955 --> 01:17:02.956
for his house.

1115
01:17:03.081 --> 01:17:04.207
Why must I run?

1116
01:17:04.457 --> 01:17:06.418
Because the Prince Regent
is going to kill you.

1117
01:17:06.793 --> 01:17:10.213
I think from Larys' experience.
those who look through you.

1118
01:17:10.255 --> 01:17:11.548
they never see you coming.

1119
01:17:11.631 --> 01:17:13.925
That's what he's trying
to say to Aegon is.

1120
01:17:13.967 --> 01:17:16.469
as long as Aegon
is not a threat.

1121
01:17:16.636 --> 01:17:18.138
he's relatively safe.

1122
01:17:18.430 --> 01:17:20.910
TOM GLYNN-CARNEY: Larys sees the light
at the end of the tunnel.

1123
01:17:20.974 --> 01:17:22.767
Or at least he's made Aegon
think he knows

1124
01:17:22.809 --> 01:17:23.977
what that could be.

1125
01:17:24.102 --> 01:17:26.896
After his encounter with Aemond
in episode six.

1126
01:17:26.980 --> 01:17:28.773
Aegon knows
that Larys is correct.

1127
01:17:29.149 --> 01:17:31.109
In that moment.
Aemond gets desperate

1128
01:17:31.151 --> 01:17:32.736
with the newfound
potential threat.

1129
01:17:32.777 --> 01:17:36.114
And he overextends
and gets forceful with Helaena.

1130
01:17:36.489 --> 01:17:40.118
PHIA SABAN: I think it's desperation
that reeks off him in that scene

1131
01:17:40.160 --> 01:17:42.495
when Alicent and Helaena
are both like.

1132
01:17:42.579 --> 01:17:44.289
"Bro. calm down.

1133
01:17:44.414 --> 01:17:48.168
This is not how somebody
who feels really sure about

1134
01:17:48.251 --> 01:17:49.794
what they're doing behaves."

1135
01:17:50.295 --> 01:17:53.340
EWAN MITCHELL: Helaena admits
she saw how I burned Aegon

1136
01:17:53.506 --> 01:17:57.177
and it's hard-hitting for Aemond
to hear he's gonna go down.

1137
01:17:57.344 --> 01:18:00.096
He kind of envisioned
after the war had finished

1138
01:18:00.180 --> 01:18:01.848
he'd be seen as this war hero.

1139
01:18:02.140 --> 01:18:04.517
But Helaena's prophecy
puts a stop to that.

1140
01:18:04.851 --> 01:18:07.812
Helaena's probably put herself
in more danger with Aemond

1141
01:18:07.854 --> 01:18:09.189
than she ever has been before.

1142
01:18:09.647 --> 01:18:11.567
- Would you not have us prevail?
- Not like this.

1143
01:18:11.858 --> 01:18:14.319
SARA: Aemond is gonna be
an interesting loose cannon

1144
01:18:14.361 --> 01:18:17.489
in season three
because when Aemond is scared.

1145
01:18:17.530 --> 01:18:20.200
laughed at. or feels small.
he lashes out.

1146
01:18:20.533 --> 01:18:22.869
You're either with him
or you're against him.

1147
01:18:23.036 --> 01:18:24.788
You get in his way.
you're in for a show.

1148
01:18:29.542 --> 01:18:32.796
ALYS RIVERS: All your life. you've sought
to command your own fate.

1149
01:18:34.214 --> 01:18:35.840
But today. you are ready.

1150
01:18:36.633 --> 01:18:38.134
RYAN: There are
different magics

1151
01:18:38.176 --> 01:18:41.012
and worlds in play here
in George's universe.

1152
01:18:41.137 --> 01:18:43.390
and Alys has been
a bit of a guide for Daemon

1153
01:18:43.515 --> 01:18:46.309
and has made him ready
for this thing

1154
01:18:46.351 --> 01:18:48.496
that Alys is going to show him
that he was not ready for

1155
01:18:48.520 --> 01:18:50.647
in episode three
when he showed up at the castle.

1156
01:18:51.189 --> 01:18:54.067
He's evolved in some way.
and he's ready

1157
01:18:54.693 --> 01:18:57.737
to see the future.

1158
01:18:58.405 --> 01:19:00.657
RYAN: We wanted Daemon to have
this final experience

1159
01:19:00.699 --> 01:19:01.759
that was undeniable to him.

1160
01:19:01.783 --> 01:19:03.663
He's somebody that has
rejected the supernatural

1161
01:19:03.702 --> 01:19:04.702
his entire life.

1162
01:19:04.869 --> 01:19:07.706
SARA: We definitely wanted
to tie what Daemon sees

1163
01:19:07.747 --> 01:19:10.250
to Game of Thrones
because where it picks up.

1164
01:19:10.333 --> 01:19:13.086
it's Daenerys Targaryen
finding those eggs.

1165
01:19:13.211 --> 01:19:16.256
She is a descendent
of Daemon and Rhaenyra

1166
01:19:16.381 --> 01:19:18.425
and so what he ends up seeing
is that

1167
01:19:18.508 --> 01:19:21.177
he's just this tiny piece
of this massive story

1168
01:19:21.219 --> 01:19:22.887
and once you start to see that.

1169
01:19:23.221 --> 01:19:25.390
you gain an entirely different
perspective.

1170
01:19:25.890 --> 01:19:30.770
This vision brings Daemon
into the story of Fire and Ice

1171
01:19:30.895 --> 01:19:32.731
and takes him to his death.

1172
01:19:32.939 --> 01:19:35.567
And after his death.
it shows him

1173
01:19:35.608 --> 01:19:38.737
that if he continues
to only think of himself.

1174
01:19:38.778 --> 01:19:40.530
great loss will be had.

1175
01:19:40.905 --> 01:19:42.741
And then he sees a hope.

1176
01:19:42.866 --> 01:19:45.702
We know it's Daenerys.
but he doesn't know who it is.

1177
01:19:46.244 --> 01:19:48.121
And he sees a White Walker.
which is cool.

1178
01:19:48.246 --> 01:19:49.598
I was like.
"Come on. that's cool."

1179
01:19:49.622 --> 01:19:51.017
RYAN: Even though Rhaenyra
and Daemon

1180
01:19:51.041 --> 01:19:53.752
are not going to save the realm
from the White Walkers.

1181
01:19:53.793 --> 01:19:55.962
their actions do have an impact

1182
01:19:56.087 --> 01:19:58.256
on how that future
is going to play out.

1183
01:19:59.466 --> 01:20:02.135
You know your path.
(ECHOING)

1184
01:20:02.969 --> 01:20:04.238
RYAN: To evolve
from the character

1185
01:20:04.262 --> 01:20:06.032
that stormed out of Dragonstone
in episode two.

1186
01:20:06.056 --> 01:20:08.475
we had to see Daemon go through
all of his... (CHUCKLES)

1187
01:20:08.892 --> 01:20:09.972
...trials and tribulations.

1188
01:20:10.101 --> 01:20:12.645
And Rhaenyra. not knowing
what Daemon is going to do.

1189
01:20:12.771 --> 01:20:14.397
And then you believe
he is changed.

1190
01:20:14.439 --> 01:20:16.316
and he sees
that he is not the player.

1191
01:20:16.441 --> 01:20:18.443
but a piece on the board.
as Alys tells him.

1192
01:20:18.610 --> 01:20:20.779
MATT SMITH: He sees Rhaenyra
on the throne.

1193
01:20:20.820 --> 01:20:24.324
and I think it gives him
the confidence in himself to go.

1194
01:20:24.449 --> 01:20:25.909
"I serve you and I'm yours."

1195
01:20:26.284 --> 01:20:28.328
SARA: And it's not that
everything's been resolved.

1196
01:20:28.453 --> 01:20:31.831
but Daemon realizes that his job
is to facilitate

1197
01:20:31.915 --> 01:20:34.334
Rhaenyra getting to the throne.
and that he...

1198
01:20:34.918 --> 01:20:39.798
understands now that Viserys
wasn't trying to punish him.

1199
01:20:39.923 --> 01:20:42.926
And so he's able to let go
of his anger at Rhaenyra.

1200
01:20:43.009 --> 01:20:44.344
To sort of let everything go
and.

1201
01:20:44.469 --> 01:20:46.638
"Let's go do this together.
I'm on your team."

1202
01:20:46.763 --> 01:20:48.598
She wasn't sure
throughout the entire season

1203
01:20:48.640 --> 01:20:51.142
if he was going to try
to set himself up as king.

1204
01:20:51.184 --> 01:20:52.453
and it's this moment
of validation

1205
01:20:52.477 --> 01:20:53.477
that she gets from him

1206
01:20:53.520 --> 01:20:55.146
that I think
is incredibly meaningful.

1207
01:20:55.438 --> 01:20:57.649
We fight for our Queen!

1208
01:20:57.691 --> 01:21:00.860
(SOLDIERS CHEER)

1209
01:21:03.822 --> 01:21:07.367
RHAENYRA: Will you see it through
and make your sacrifice?

1210
01:21:08.034 --> 01:21:09.369
A son for a son?

1211
01:21:11.287 --> 01:21:13.307
You've seen the massive ways
that things have changed

1212
01:21:13.331 --> 01:21:15.142
between meeting number one
and meeting number two.

1213
01:21:15.166 --> 01:21:17.877
And I think both of them have
been through further trauma.

1214
01:21:18.169 --> 01:21:20.463
and it's brought them back
around to a place

1215
01:21:20.505 --> 01:21:22.007
where they're wondering
what the cost

1216
01:21:22.132 --> 01:21:23.216
of all this is for.

1217
01:21:23.675 --> 01:21:26.219
It's massive that Alicent
travels to Rhaenyra.

1218
01:21:26.344 --> 01:21:27.512
It's treason.

1219
01:21:27.637 --> 01:21:30.056
If Aemond found out.
head on a spike.

1220
01:21:30.181 --> 01:21:32.017
But it's also to look Rhaenyra
in the eye

1221
01:21:32.392 --> 01:21:34.352
as my. like. rawest self.

1222
01:21:34.394 --> 01:21:37.022
"This is me shedding
whatever power

1223
01:21:37.063 --> 01:21:38.815
or Queenly status I had.

1224
01:21:38.898 --> 01:21:39.983
I was wrong.
Take it.

1225
01:21:40.025 --> 01:21:42.068
I don't want anything
to do with it. I'm done."

1226
01:21:42.527 --> 01:21:45.196
She's had this journey
of self-actualization.

1227
01:21:45.238 --> 01:21:46.798
and she's got a lot
of power within her.

1228
01:21:46.865 --> 01:21:50.243
And I think she feels
much more capable.

1229
01:21:50.702 --> 01:21:53.538
It's funny to be offered
a huge gift

1230
01:21:53.747 --> 01:21:56.249
at the point where you think
you already have what you need.

1231
01:21:56.750 --> 01:21:59.377
SARA: The climax of that scene
is Rhaenyra.

1232
01:21:59.419 --> 01:22:00.920
"I'm going to have to kill
your son."

1233
01:22:01.046 --> 01:22:02.714
and Alicent acceding to it.

1234
01:22:02.756 --> 01:22:05.342
Which is huge for Rhaenyra
because that is not something

1235
01:22:05.425 --> 01:22:07.552
that Alicent
would ever have done before.

1236
01:22:07.594 --> 01:22:10.055
So I think that causes her
to really believe

1237
01:22:10.096 --> 01:22:11.389
what Alicent is saying.

1238
01:22:11.598 --> 01:22:13.725
Rhaenyra has
these new dragon riders.

1239
01:22:13.933 --> 01:22:17.020
she's just gotten Daemon back.
she has this big army.

1240
01:22:17.103 --> 01:22:18.271
If she wanted to.

1241
01:22:18.355 --> 01:22:20.940
she could probably win
this war herself.

1242
01:22:21.441 --> 01:22:24.194
But at the cost of thousands
and thousands of lives.

1243
01:22:24.444 --> 01:22:27.113
And then she's sort of given
this backdoor by Alicent.

1244
01:22:27.238 --> 01:22:28.948
And so I think we leave
season two

1245
01:22:29.032 --> 01:22:33.703
with Rhaenyra in this place of.
"What am I going to do?"

1246
01:22:34.746 --> 01:22:36.122
RYAN: It's such
a beautiful scene.

1247
01:22:36.247 --> 01:22:37.624
and so wonderfully written
by Sara.

1248
01:22:37.791 --> 01:22:39.584
wonderfully performed by Emma
and Olivia.

1249
01:22:39.709 --> 01:22:41.461
and Geeta
beautifully directed it.

1250
01:22:41.586 --> 01:22:43.546
And the way it launches us
into the third season

1251
01:22:43.630 --> 01:22:45.298
and the unknown
of what's to come.

1252
01:22:45.423 --> 01:22:46.716
it's a tour de force.

1253
01:22:47.300 --> 01:22:49.719
♪ (DELICATE PIANO MUSIC PLAYS)

1254
01:22:49.803 --> 01:22:52.263
SARA: There's so much in play.
there are armies.

1255
01:22:52.305 --> 01:22:55.433
there are dragons.
there's castle strongholds

1256
01:22:55.558 --> 01:22:58.561
and political maneuvering.
but at the end of the day.

1257
01:22:58.603 --> 01:23:01.564
it comes down to these two women
trying to figure it out.

1258
01:23:02.065 --> 01:23:03.918
RYAN: The Lannisters
are arriving in the Riverlands.

1259
01:23:03.942 --> 01:23:05.819
The Hightowers are marching
through the Reach.

1260
01:23:05.944 --> 01:23:07.946
The Winter Wolves
are coming from the North.

1261
01:23:08.071 --> 01:23:09.489
The Triarchy's sailing.

1262
01:23:09.614 --> 01:23:11.741
We see the Seasnake
going back out to sea.

1263
01:23:11.908 --> 01:23:13.618
Daemon has his army
in the Riverlands.

1264
01:23:13.827 --> 01:23:15.745
Alicent's fourth son
on his dragon.

1265
01:23:15.829 --> 01:23:17.997
The Blue Queen is now flying
in support

1266
01:23:18.123 --> 01:23:20.250
of this massive
Hightower army.

1267
01:23:20.333 --> 01:23:22.127
We find Otto
in this cell somewhere.

1268
01:23:22.168 --> 01:23:23.437
and we don't know quite
where he is

1269
01:23:23.461 --> 01:23:24.963
or what happened to him.

1270
01:23:25.255 --> 01:23:27.298
GEETA:
Rhaena discovers a dragon.

1271
01:23:27.340 --> 01:23:29.926
And we see a forest
outside of King's Landing.

1272
01:23:29.968 --> 01:23:31.344
And there is Aegon.

1273
01:23:31.511 --> 01:23:33.596
Larys and Aegon
basically escape King's Landing

1274
01:23:33.638 --> 01:23:35.181
as shit's about to hit
the fan.

1275
01:23:35.765 --> 01:23:38.518
It's just a reminder of
things have been put in motion

1276
01:23:38.601 --> 01:23:40.020
which they can't pull back.

1277
01:23:40.145 --> 01:23:43.189
And similar to Daemon's vision.
where you're seeing the things

1278
01:23:43.273 --> 01:23:44.983
that are all going to come
to play a part

1279
01:23:45.025 --> 01:23:46.026
in the whole story.

1280
01:23:46.526 --> 01:23:49.154
While this season was very much
about the fits and starts

1281
01:23:49.195 --> 01:23:50.530
of an early medieval war.

1282
01:23:50.613 --> 01:23:53.324
season three is clearly
going to be about total war.

1283
01:23:53.867 --> 01:23:56.202
I think Team Black
are in ascendancy.

1284
01:23:56.327 --> 01:23:58.204
A desperate Aemond
is a dangerous Aemond.

1285
01:23:58.288 --> 01:23:59.873
I will never. ever concede.

1286
01:23:59.956 --> 01:24:02.375
The whole thing is just
so volatile.

1287
01:24:02.667 --> 01:24:04.044
Baela's gonna do
whatever it takes.

1288
01:24:04.169 --> 01:24:06.171
whatever it comes down to.
she's prepared to do.

1289
01:24:06.546 --> 01:24:07.857
EMMA D'ARCY:
She has the better hand

1290
01:24:07.881 --> 01:24:11.343
and an inevitably positive shot
at the throne.

1291
01:24:11.634 --> 01:24:13.754
TOM: The pendulum could swing
either way very quickly.

1292
01:24:13.970 --> 01:24:16.514
We shall see who
the last man standing is.

1293
01:24:16.556 --> 01:24:18.725
♪ (THRILLING OUTRO MUSIC
PLAYS) ♪
